and%20search%20%26quot%3B55%20inch%20TV%20stand%26quot%3B%20on%20Google%2C%20I%20can%20see%20seemingly%20infinite%20options%20of%20stands%20that%20match%20that%20description.%20If%20I%20want%20to%20keep%20scrolling%20through%2C%20I%20can%20open%20Google%20Shopping%20which%20now%20operates%20more%20like%20a%20third-party%20marketplace%2C%20thanks%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-shopping-ai-features-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20revamp%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222788%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20Shopping%20screenshot%20showing%2055-inch%20TV%20stands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67730314ca1058716a5ebe94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20I%20search%20%26quot%3B55-inch%20TV%20stand%2C%26quot%3B%20I'm%20met%20with%20countless%20options%20of%20relevant%20products.%3Cp%3Escreenshot%2FGoogle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%20Search%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20responded%20to%20my%20search%20with%20around%205%20products%20and%20linked%20additional%20sites%20in%20the%20source%20tab.%20Instead%20of%20seeing%20a%20visual%20array%20of%20products%20from%20different%20brands%20with%20filters%20to%20set%20my%20preferences%2C%20ChatGPT%20Search%20selected%20some.%20I%20also%20found%20the%20source%20tab%20to%20be%20a%20fairly%20narrow%20display%20that%20didn't%20present%20sources%20in%20a%20particularly%20helpful%20way%20visually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222210%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22screenshot%20showing%20ChatGPT%20Search%20results%20for%20tv%20stand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676eda51bec2d3fdefeb2fee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221312%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScreenshot%20of%20a%20ChatGPT%20Search%20of%2055-inch%20TV%20stands.%3Cp%3Escreenshot%2FChatGPT%20Search%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20it's%20worth%20noting%20that%20some%20people%20may%20prefer%20the%20approach%20of%20ChatGPT%20Search%20to%20their%20usual%20search%20engine.%20And%20Google%20has%20been%20evolving%20the%20search%20experience%20over%20the%20past%20year%20as%20it%20leans%20into%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20an%20argument%20to%20be%20made%20about%20too%20many%20options%20being%20shown%20on%20Google%2C%20and%20ChatGPT%20certainly%20narrows%20it%20down.%20However%2C%20if%20I'm%20doing%20a%20broad%20search%2C%20I%20personally%20want%20to%20see%20the%20breadth%20of%20what's%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20using%20ChatGPT%20Search%2C%20I%20found%20that%20I%20missed%20Google's%20layout%20of%20providing%20AI%20Overviews%20at%20the%20top%20of%20some%20queries.%20The%20feature%20allows%20users%20to%20get%20the%20short%20version%20while%20also%20having%20the%20option%20to%20scroll%20through%20other%20sources%2C%20which%20I%20feel%20offers%20a%20bit%20more%20agency%20in%20how%20users%20consume%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228ae59142-b9e2-49c9-a2a5-8c822fd9e687%5C%22%3EGoogle%20is%20optimized%20for%20keyword%20searches%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20experiment%2C%20I%20often%20opened%20a%20separate%20browser%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20my%20primary%20Search%20engine%20because%20ChatGPT%20Search%20took%20longer%20to%20provide%20the%20answers%20I%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20tech%20giant%20has%20dominated%20the%20search%20engine%20space%20for%20years%2C%20so%20my%20habits%20are%20naturally%20optimized%20for%20Google%20Search.%20I'm%20used%20to%20typing%20in%20a%20single%20keyword%20and%20instantly%20finding%20an%20array%20of%20relevant%20links.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-ai-announcement-gemini-io-event-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20head%20of%20search%2C%20Liz%20Reid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20at%20Google%20I%2FO%20in%20May%20that%20%26quot%3BGoogle%20will%20do%20the%20Googling%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20I've%20generally%20found%20that%20to%20be%20true.%20When%20I%20look%20up%20a%20company%2C%20person%2C%20or%20website%2C%20I'm%20able%20to%20see%20social%20media%20accounts%2C%20recent%20news%2C%20and%20other%20relevant%20links.%20I%20can%20also%20select%20filters%20or%20categories%20such%20as%20images%2C%20videos%2C%20news%2C%20and%20shopping%20to%20narrow%20my%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%20Search%20worked%20better%20when%20I%20had%20a%20specific%20prompt%20or%20question%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20I%20have%20an%20open-ended%20research%20query%2C%20like%20%26quot%3BWhat%20was%20President%20Gerald%20Ford's%20most%20notable%20accomplishment%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BHow%20did%20Gerald%20Ford's%20legacy%20differ%20from%20other%20presidents%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20would%20probably%20turn%20to%20ChatGPT%20Search%20because%20it%20can%20organize%20information%20concisely%2C%20and%20save%20me%20from%20reading%20hundreds%20of%20related%20articles%20that%20might%20not%20address%20that%20specific%20question%20or%20contain%20those%20keywords.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20lead%20in%20offering%20keyword-based%20access%20to%20the%20wider%20web%20is%20tough%20to%20beat.%20While%20I%20see%20valuable%20uses%20for%20both%20products%2C%20I%20don't%20see%20how%20ChatGPT%20Search%20could%20replace%20for%20me%20what%20Google%20has%20spent%20decades%20building%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20at%20this%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-search-default-web-browser-engine-compared-google-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735639381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677328076b318443a944e7a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-search-default-web-browser-engine-compared-google-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22ChatGPT%20Search%20helps%20users%20find%20quick%20answers%20based%20on%20up-to-date%20information%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20kept%20returning%20to%20Google.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-search-default-web-browser-engine-compared-google-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2211%20Reddit%20execs%20describe%20their%20wild%20ride%20in%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Reddit%20logo%20with%20an%20emoji%20hand%20on%20it's%20chin%20to%20look%20like%20it's%20thinking%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6765a0a36c531c315b8991df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReddit%20executives%20we%20spoke%20to%20said%20they%20balanced%20stress%20and%20excitement%20as%20Reddit%20went%20public%20in%202024.%3Cp%3EReddit%3B%20iStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EReddit%20went%20public%20in%202024%20and%20is%20a%20more%20popular%2C%20profitable%20site%20than%20ever%20in%20its%2020-year%20history.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBI%20spoke%20to%2011%20Reddit%20execs%20about%20how%20they've%20handled%20new%20challenges%20while%20maintaining%20a%20beloved%20culture.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20shared%20everything%20from%20their%20favorite%20subreddit%20to%20what%20the%20IPO%20means%20to%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E2024%20was%20a%20great%20year%20for%20Reddit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20went%20public%20in%20March%20with%20a%20%246.4%20billion%20valuation%20and%20reported%20its%20first%20quarterly%20profit%20in%20October.%20Shares%20have%20soared%20230%25%20since%20its%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20BI's%20Emily%20Stewart%20recently%20wrote%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-mainstream-google-traffic-stock-revenue-human-users-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20has%20become%20more%20mainstream%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0than%20ever.%20Its%20daily%20active%20users%20jumped%2047%25%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20quarter%20compared%20to%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20an%20unprecedented%20number%20of%20people%20tacking%20%26quot%3BReddit%26quot%3B%20onto%20their%20search%20terms%20%E2%80%94%20a%20demand%20the%20company%20will%20try%20to%20meet%20with%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-answers-how-it-works-performs-early-access-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20Answers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20its%20new%20AI-powered%20search%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20find%20out%20what%20this%20year%20has%20looked%20like%20on%20the%20inside%2C%20BI%20asked%2011%20Reddit%20executives%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%26quot%3BSnoos%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Reddit%20calls%20its%202%2C000%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20to%20share%20their%20favorite%20highlights%20behind%20the%20scenes%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bfront%20page%20of%20the%20internet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20described%20some%20career-defining%20moments%20and%20talked%20about%20managing%20through%20rapid%20change%20and%20a%20new%20level%20of%20pressure.%20Here's%20what%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reddit%20execs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676d9873a3e82c7912046f59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThree%20of%2011%20Reddit%20execs%20BI%20spoke%20to%20(from%20left%20to%20right)%3A%20Roxy%20Young%2C%20Laura%20Nestler%2C%20and%20Serkan%20Piantino.%3Cp%3EReddit%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6d95de9-3776-4dd5-ae44-9beabf0a53cd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20it%20meant%20to%20take%20Reddit%20public%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20pretend%20that%20this%20all%20makes%20sense%2C%20and%20it's%20all%20business%20as%20usual%20for%20a%20little%20bit.%20But%20there%20are%20moments%20where%20I%20kind%20of%20zone%20out%20and%20realize%20the%20scale%20and%20how%20cool%20a%20moment%20I'm%20in.%20I%20guess%20the%20word%20to%20describe%20it%20is%20'awe.'%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3ESerkan%20Piantino%2C%2041%2C%20VP%20of%20product%2C%20New%20York%20City.%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20always%20going%20to%20be%20individuals%20that%20say%2C%20'Reddit%20is%20not%20what%20it%20used%20to%20be.'%20Of%20course%2C%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20what%20it%20used%20to%20be.%20It's%20going%20to%20be%20what%20we%20make%20it%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EDavid%20Trencher%2C%2043%2C%20senior%20managing%20director%2C%20large%20customer%20sales%2C%20EMEA%20%26amp%3B%20Australia%2C%20London.%20Joined%20the%20company%20in%202019.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B2024%20has%20been%20maybe%20the%20highlight%20of%20my%20career%20at%20Reddit.%20We%20are%20so%20focused%20on%20starting%20with%20community.%20I%20think%20in%20'24%20we've%20embraced%20that%20value%20more%20than%20ever%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Laura%20Nestler%2C%20VP%20of%20community%2C%20Seattle.%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225eaf9125-c2e0-409d-8f94-b774acefb582%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIPO%20day%20was%20'so%20Reddit%2C'%20execs%20said%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224862%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reddit%20Listing%20Day%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676d96997236dcf54aa262de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223241%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReddit%20employees%20gather%20at%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%20for%20listing%20day.%3Cp%3ENYSE%3A%20RDDT%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGetting%20Snoo%20(the%20company's%20mascot)%20to%20ring%20the%20bell%20(rather%20than%20our%20CEO)%20was%20just%20so%20Reddit-y.%20It%20was%20a%20culmination%20of%20so%20many%20years%20of%20hard%20work%20to%20get%20here%2C%20and%20to%20see%20it%20all%20come%20to%20fruition%20in%20a%20very%20Reddit%20way%20was%20awesome.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%3Cem%3E%20Paulita%20David%2C%20Senior%20Managing%20Director%2C%20large%20customer%20sales%20in%20North%20America.%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20broadcast%20live%20globally%2C%20and%20I%20got%20to%20emcee%20the%20entire%20thing%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange.%20We%20all%20got%20to%20see%20and%20feel%20what%20was%20happening.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EMichelle%20Lozzi%2C%2040%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20experience%2C%20San%20Francisco.%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202017.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20so%20nice%20having%20our%20new%20Snoo%20mascot%20up%20there%20ringing%20the%20bell%2C%20symbolizing%20our%20employees%20and%20the%20community.%20There%20is%20a%20human%20in%20there.%20We%20cannot%20reveal%20who%20it%20is%2C%20but%20the%20only%20clue%20I%20can%20share%20is%20you%20have%20to%20be%205'10%26quot%3B%20to%20wear%20the%20suit.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EMonica%20Benson%2C%2038%2C%20head%20of%20brand%20operations%20and%20creative%20production%2C%20Los%20Angeles.%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202020.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2289566fd1-d898-4b73-b6e4-3ee71a0c42ab%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20execs%20managed%20through%20change%20and%20volatility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20change%20for%20us%20has%20been%20just%20the%20sheer%20volume%20of%20advertisers%20wanting%20to%20advertise%20on%20Reddit.%20It%20impacts%20my%20job%20pretty%20dramatically.%20With%20this%20increased%20demand%2C%20we're%20really%20embracing%20more%20automation.%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%94%20David%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20run%20a%20lot%20of%20experiments%2C%20so%20failure%20is%20a%20day-to-day%20thing.%20Many%20of%20our%20experiments%20just%20don't%20pan%20out%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20job%20is%20to%20refine%20the%20idea%20and%20keep%20going%20or%20decide%20to%20work%20on%20something%20else.%20We're%20not%20a%20huge%20company.%20We%20still%20have%20limited%20resources%2C%20so%20we%20have%20to%20prioritize.%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%94%20Piantino%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20balance%20of%20excitement%20and%20pressure%20that%20keeps%20me%20grounded.%20The%20fact%20that%20we%20have%20a%20real%20share%20price%20that%20we%20can%20use%20to%20measure%20our%20size%20adds%20somewhat%20to%20the%20pressure%2C%20but%20ultimately%20the%20excitement%20and%20enthusiasm%20outweigh%20it.%20Something%20we%20try%20to%20instill%20in%20our%20culture%20is%20to%20not%20get%20too%20high%20with%20the%20highs%2C%20and%20too%20low%20with%20the%20lows.%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Jesse%20Rose%2C%2038%2C%20head%20of%20investor%20relations%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20what%20volatility%20looks%20like%2C%20and%20I%20know%20how%20much%20that%20can%20be%20a%20distraction%20for%20the%20team.%20I%20liked%20being%20a%20calming%20force%20and%20reminding%20people%20that%2C%20some%20days%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20say%20great%20things%20about%20you.%20Some%20days%20they're%20going%20to%20say%20bad%20things%20about%20you%2C%20but%20you%20are%20never%20as%20good%20or%20as%20bad%20as%20they%20say%20you%20are.%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Piantino%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20(two-year%20pre-IPO%20period)%20helped%20us%20prepare%20our%20teams%2C%20which%20helped%20alleviate%20some%20stress.%20We%20were%20going%20into%20it%20knowing%20what%20we%20needed%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3ETrencher%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20our%20communities%20are%20growing%20really%20fast%2C%20and%20that%20can%20be%20a%20challenge.%20There%20are%20a%20bunch%20of%20tools%20that%20moderators%20can%20now%20use%20to%20handle%20moments%20of%20accelerated%20growth.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3ENicole%20Heard%2C%2036%2C%20UK%20country%20lead%2C%20London.%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ad2e7314-ad34-4581-8040-a5281b8fa495%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EExecs%20say%20Reddit's%20culture%20hasn't%20changed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20came%20back%20from%20maternity%20leave%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20how%20the%20company%20culture%20had%20changed.%20It%20felt%20warm%20to%20come%20back%20to%20that%20authentic%2C%20community-building%20company%2C%20but%20the%20stakes%20are%20higher.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EBenson%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20in%20our%20UK%20office%20genuinely%20like%20spending%20time%20with%20each%20other.%20Our%20office%20had%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20real-life%20visits%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20probably%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20The%20people%20and%20culture%20is%20what%20makes%20it%20an%20amazing%20place%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%94%20Sam%20Hughes%2C%2033%2C%20senior%20client%20partner%2C%20London%2C%20Joined%20Reddit%20in%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20joined%20in%202021%2C%20we%20had%20this%20really%20small%20kind%20of%20Harry%20Potter%20cupboard%20at%20a%20WeWork%20that%20sat%20three%20to%20five%20people.%20Then%20we%20got%20a%20bigger%20space%20with%20a%20whole%20floor%2C%20and%20now%2C%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20we%20got%20an%20amazing%20new%20building.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20Hughes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20hosted%20Mod%20World%20in%20our%20San%20Francisco%20office%2C%20which%20was%20where%20we%20brought%20in%2060%20of%20our%20moderators%20and%20made%20them%20feel%20like%20they're%20also%20a%20part%20of%20this.%20Because%20it's