p%2C%20whose%20palm%20oil%20has%20ended%20up%20in%20products%20ranging%20from%20Cheetos%20to%20Colgate%20toothpaste.%20The%20%24160%20million%20that%20the%20company's%20backers%2C%20primarily%20US%20venture%20capitalists%20and%20private%20equity%20funds%2C%20have%20spent%20on%20its%20operations%20represents%20the%20largest%20foreign%20investment%20in%20agriculture%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20Peruvian%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20palm%20industry%20got%20off%20the%20ground%20here%20thanks%20to%20US%20development%20programs%20designed%20to%20give%20farmers%20a%20money-making%20alternative%20to%20growing%20coca%20plants%2C%20the%20precursor%20to%20cocaine%2C%20and%20the%20US%20ambassador%20to%20Peru%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FUSAmbPeru%2Fstatus%2F1641218685481234437%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20a%20visit%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Ocho%20Sur's%20properties%20last%20year.%20Ocho%20Sur's%20operations%20are%20now%20so%20vast%2C%20and%20it%20is%20such%20a%20dominant%20force%20in%20the%20region's%20economy%2C%20that%20locals%20refer%20to%20it%20simply%20as%20%3Cem%3Ela%20empresa%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthe%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Palm%20oil%20factory%20of%20Ocho%20Sur.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762e1336c531c315b88e933%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOcho%20Sur's%20Tibecocha%20oil%20palm%20plantation%20in%20Ucayali%2C%20Peru.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20plantations%20came%20at%20a%20steep%20price.%20To%20make%20way%20for%20those%20industrial%20fields%20of%20palm%20trees%2C%20some%2030%2C000%20acres%20of%20rainforest%20were%20cut%20down%2C%20a%20swath%20of%20destruction%20that%20one%20Indigenous%20leader%20called%20an%20act%20of%20%26quot%3Beco-genocide.%26quot%3B%20Biologists%20from%20Chicago's%20Field%20Museum%20have%20ranked%20the%20rugged%20mountains%20that%20rise%20west%20of%20the%20plantations%20%26quot%3Bamong%20the%20most%20diverse%20of%20all%20conservation%20areas%20in%20Peru.%26quot%3B%20When%20the%20museum's%20team%20surveyed%20the%20region%20for%20three%20weeks%20in%202000%2C%20it%20tallied%201%2C600%20species%20of%20plants%2C%2071%20species%20of%20mammals%2C%20and%20more%20than%20500%20species%20of%20birds.%20At%20least%2028%20species%20were%20new%20to%20science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%201960s%2C%20more%20than%2013%25%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maaproject.org%2F2022%2Famazon-tipping-point%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20original%20Amazonian%20rainforest%20has%20been%20cleared.%20Most%20of%20the%20destruction%20has%20been%20concentrated%20in%20Brazil%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maapprogram.org%2Famazon-tipping-point%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeru%20is%20second%20on%20the%20list%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20the%20destruction%20continues%2C%20Thomas%20Lovejoy%2C%20a%20former%20biodiversity%20advisor%20to%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20Amazon%20could%20reach%20a%20tipping%20point%20and%20become%20too%20hot%2C%20dry%2C%20and%20fire-prone%20to%20remain%20a%20rainforest.%20Without%20the%20carbon-absorbing%20capacity%20of%20the%20Amazon%2C%20the%20world%20would%20face%20increasing%20temperatures%20and%20melting%20the%20ice%20caps%2C%20making%20cities%20as%20far%20away%20as%20Mumbai%20virtually%20unlivable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20was%20produced%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthefern.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFood%20%26amp%3B%20Environment%20Reporting%20Network%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20independent%2C%20nonprofit%20news%20organization.%20Field%20reporting%20was%20supported%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpulitzercenter.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPulitzer%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3ESeeking%20to%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fochosur.com%2Fen%2Fsustainability%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emodel%20of%20sustainable%20development%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Ocho%20Sur%20has%20signed%20pacts%20with%20local%20communities%20to%20conserve%20the%20native%20ecosystem%2C%20and%20its%20polished%20English-language%20website%20features%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fochosur.com%2Fen%2Fgalleries%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslideshow%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20anteaters%2C%20sloths%2C%20and%20monkeys.%20The%20company%20has%20replaced%20its%20trucks%20and%20tractors%20with%20mules%20and%20water%20buffalo%20and%20has%20vowed%20not%20to%20expand%20its%20operations%20into%20standing%20forest.%20Over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20Ocho%20Sur%20says%2C%20it%20has%20spent%20%243%20million%20maintaining%20roads%20and%20building%20schools%20and%20medical%20clinics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20company's%20CEO%2C%20Michael%20Spoor%2C%20who%20joined%20Ocho%20Sur%20in%202019%2C%20talks%20about%20the%20company's%20accomplishments%2C%20he%20draws%20a%20sharp%20line%20between%20the%20Ocho%20Sur%20Group%20and%20whoever%20it%20was%20who%20first%20staked%20a%20claim%20in%20the%20virgin%20territory.%20%26quot%3BWe%20came%20to%20Peru%20in%202016%20and%20bought%20two%20farms%20in%20Ucayali%20at%20a%20public%20auction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20has%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20that%20we%20have%20done%2C%20we%20have%20done%20without%20deforesting%20anything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Updated%20Ocho%20Sur%20P%20Edit%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2F7s7LpY1Y-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EDocuments%20I%20obtained%20from%20a%20criminal%20investigation%20into%20Ocho%20Sur%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20an%20exclusive%20trove%20of%20internal%20company%20emails%2C%20bank%20records%2C%20and%20spreadsheets%20covering%20eight%20years%20of%20plantation%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20tell%20a%20more%20complex%20story%20about%20the%20role%20of%20the%20company's%20founders%20in%20the%20original%20destruction%20of%20the%20rainforest.%20At%20its%20heart%20is%20an%20American%20businessman%20named%20Dennis%20Melka%2C%20who%20a%20Peruvian%20prosecutor%20has%20claimed%20is%20the%20ringleader%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bcriminal%20organization%26quot%3B%20that%20passed%20mature%20plantations%20from%20one%20company%20his%20investors%20had%20bankrolled%2C%20United%20Oils%2C%20onto%20a%20second%2C%20Ocho%20Sur.%20After%20the%20transfer%2C%20I%20found%2C%20key%20personnel%20from%20United%20Oils%20remained%20in%20place%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Melka.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20prosecutors%20say%20that%20United%20Oils%20illegally%20cleared%20much%20of%20the%20plantation%20land%2C%20and%20that%20Ocho%20Sur%2C%20for%20all%20of%20its%20sustainable%20initiatives%2C%20is%20in%20many%20respects%20the%20same%20entity%20as%20its%20clear-cutting%20predecessor.%20Melka%20has%20not%20responded%20publicly%20to%20the%20prosecutors'%20allegations%20and%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOcho%20Sur's%20links%20to%20deforestation%20have%20profound%20implications%20for%20businesses%2C%20consumers%2C%20and%20the%20environment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20exactly%20counts%20as%20%26quot%3Bsustainability%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20palm%20oil%20industry.%20The%20global%20market%20for%20palm%20oil%2C%20valued%20at%20more%20than%20%2470%20billion%20last%20year%2C%20is%20experiencing%20steady%20growth%2C%20driven%20by%20its%20use%20in%20products%20as%20varied%20as%20food%2C%20beverages%2C%20biofuels%2C%20and%20cosmetics.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20passed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenvironment.ec.europa.eu%2Ftopics%2Fforests%2Fdeforestation%2Fregulation-deforestation-free-products_en%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20deforestation%20that%20promised%20to%20be%20the%20strictest%20in%20the%20world.%20Companies%20like%20Ocho%20Sur%20are%20now%20racing%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20their%20plantations%20were%20not%20illegally%20deforested%20%E2%80%94%20or%20risk%20losing%20their%20share%20of%20the%20lucrative%20market.%20But%20it%20may%20not%20be%20that%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNearly%20everything%20they%20export%20has%20been%20illegally%20produced%2C%26quot%3B%20Julia%20Urrunaga%2C%20who%20leads%20research%20in%20Peru%20for%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC-based%20environmental%20organization%2C%20argues.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20needs%20to%20happen%20here%20is%20they%20need%20to%20be%20sanctioned%2C%20and%20they%20need%20to%20be%20ordered%20to%20reforest%20and%20leave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Spoor%2C%20General%20Manager%20of%20Ocho%20Sur.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762f2545cddac6581d69eb4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Spoor%20at%20the%20Tibecocha%20plantation.%20He's%20been%20Ocho%20Sur's%20CEO%20since%202019.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20Michael%20Spoor%20invited%20me%20to%20spend%20a%20few%20days%20visiting%20Ocho%20Sur's%20plantations%20and%20the%20surrounding%20communities.%20The%20company%20was%20losing%20buyers%20left%20and%20right.%20That%20month%2C%20PepsiCo%2C%20which%20had%20used%20Ocho%20Sur%20palm%20oil%20in%20its%20Cheetos%20and%20Doritos%2C%20became%20the%20latest%20global%20brand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fojo-publico.com%2F5076%2Focho-surs-links-palm-oil-supplier-multinational-pepsico%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20be%20named%20in%20the%20media%20over%20the%20historic%20deforestation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Spoor%20was%20eager%20to%20tell%20his%20side%20of%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20headquarters%20are%20on%20the%20fifth%20floor%20of%20the%20Wyndham%20hotel%20in%20the%20regional%20capital%20of%20Pucallpa%2C%20a%20city%20of%20300%2C000%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Ucayali%20River.%20When%20I%20met%20Spoor%20in%20the%20lobby%20one%20morning%2C%20he%20was%20wearing%20what%20passes%20for%20executive%20attire%20in%20these%20parts%3A%20a%20loose%20nylon%20shirt%2C%20khaki%20pants%2C%20and%20hiking%20boots.%20He%20looked%20more%20like%20a%20tourist%20heading%20off%20to%20hike%20the%20ruins%20of%20Machu%20Picchu%20than%20the%20head%20of%20a%20palm%20oil%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20son%20of%20a%20Protestant%20minister%20in%20Iowa%2C%20Spoor%20earned%20a%20degree%20in%20civil%20engineering%20before%20working%20for%20Exxon%20and%20leading%20companies%20that%20recycled%20spent%20oils%20and%20other%20industrial%20waste.%20One%20of%20his%20operations%2C%20NewStream%2C%20which%20Spoor%20ran%20from%202008%20to%202014%2C%20was%20accused%20by%20the%20Massachusetts%20attorney%20general%20of%20illegally%20dumping%20wastewater%20tainted%20with%20lead%2C%20chromium%2C%20and%20other%20hazardous%20chemicals%20into%20a%20municipal%20treatment%20facility%20that%20flows%20into%20the%20Ten%20Mile%20River.%20In%20April%202014%2C%20Spoor%20signed%20a%20consent%20decree%20on%20behalf%20of%20NewStream%20to%20settle%20the%20case%20and%20the%20company%20paid%20a%20fine%3B%20he%20has%20denied%20that%20NewStream%20released%20any%20hazardous%20waste.%20Two%20months%20later%2C%20he%20headed%20to%20Latin%20America.%20His%20first%20stop%20was%20Mexico%2C%20to%20run%20another%20waste%20recycler.%20Then%2C%20in%202019%2C%20he%20joined%20Ocho%20Sur%20to%20oversee%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20cleanup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20accepting%20the%20position%2C%20Spoor%20visited%20the%20plantations%20with%20one%20of%20Ocho%20Sur's%20shareholders.%20He%20marveled%20at%20the%20efficiency%20of%20the%20African%20oil%20palm%2C%20which%20can%20produce%20five%20times%20as%20much%20edible%20oil%20per%20acre%20as%20corn%20or%20soy.%20Every%2010%20days%2C%20each%20tree%20develops%20a%2050-pound%20cluster%20of%20fruits%20oozing%20with%20thick%2C%20red%20oil.%20They%20will%20keep%20producing%20for%20the%20next%2020%20years.%20The%20catch%20is%20that%20oil%20palm%20can%20be%20profitably%20grown%20only%20within%2010%20degrees%20of%20the%20equator%2C%20a%20region%20that%20overlaps%20with%20the%20planet's%20most%20biodiverse%20ecosystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20environmental%20activists%20raised%20the%20alarm%20about%20the%20palm%20oil%20industry's%20toll%20on%20the%20tropical%20forests%20of%20Southeast%20Asia%20two%20decades%20ago%2C%20Unilever%2C%20the%20world's%20largest%20buyer%20of%20palm%20oil%2C%20teamed%20up%20with%20the%20World%20Wildlife%20Fund%20and%20other%20parties%20to%20establish%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frspo.org%2Fwho-we-are%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoundtable%20on%20Sustainable%20Palm%20Oil%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20roundtable%20launched%20a%20program%20in%202007%20that%20certifies%20growers%20whose%20plantations%20are%20not%20on%20recently%20deforested%20or%20contested%20lands.%20Only%20a%20fifth%20of%20palm%20oil%20sold%20across%20the%20globe%20was%20certified%20by%202022.%20Spoor's%20mission%20was%20to%20get%20Ocho%20Sur's%20crop%20certified%20as%20deforestation-free%2C%20but%20exactly%20what%20that%20means%20depends%20on%20when%20you%20start%20the%20clock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpoor%20and%20I%20headed%20out%20of%20Pucallpa%20in%20a%20four-wheel-drive%20truck%20driven%20by%20Krassimir%20Doldourov%2C%20a%20chain-smoking%20Bulgarian%20who%20oversees%20the%20plantation's%20road%20maintenance%20work.%20After%20an%20hour%2C%20Doldourov%20swung%20onto%20a%20dirt%20road%20with%20tire-swallowing%20holes.%20We%20passed%20abandoned%20farms%2C%20cattle%20pastures%2C%20and%20stray%20dogs%2C%20but%20not%20much%20forest.%20Finally%2C%20Doldourov%20maneuvered%20the%20truck%20down%20the%20scoured%20bank%20of%20a%20large%2C%20brown%20river%2C%20a%20tributary%20to%20the%20Ucayali%2C%20and%20onto%20the%20platform%20of%20Ocho%20Sur's%20pontoon-style%20ferry%2C%20powered%20by%20two%20outboard%20motors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20river%2C%20we%20passed%20a%20series%20of%20signs%20Spoor%20had%20installed%20when%20he%20took%20the%20job.%20%26quot%3BWe%20work%20in%20harmony%20with%20nature%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20one.%20%26quot%3BWe%20protect%20wildlife%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20another.%20%26quot%3BWe%20conserve%20forests%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20a%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Julia%20Urrunaga.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762e1ad0a6d56a4f9c1c9e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJulia%20Urrunaga%2C%20who%20leads%20research%20in%20Peru%20for%20the%20Environmental%20Investigation%20Agency%2C%20says%20of%20Ocho%20Sur%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20need%20to%20be%20ordered%20to%20reforest%20and%20leave.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Spoor%20pointed%20out%2C%20most%20deforestation%20in%20the%20Peruvian%20Amazon%20today%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D110a9c271f4834be34b68e78eb100fccf2fe81dcbef2b3869c8a9ba2bd50f78f%26postID%3D6758d4c6b942454853528030%26postSlug%3Dus-investors-and-the-destruction-of-peru-rainforest-2024-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-018-19358-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomes%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20small-scale%20farmers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he%20wanted%20to%20convince%20me%20that%20industrial%20agriculture%2C%20which%20had%20deepened%20climate%20impacts%20elsewhere%2C%20could%20achieve%20the%20opposite%20here.%20Ocho%20Sur%20is%20the%20largest%20formal%20employer%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Ucayali%20and%20accounts%20for%20about%20half%20of%20its%20exports%2C%20meaning%20that%20it%20provides%20economic%20opportunities%20to%20thousands%20of%20people%20who%20might%20otherwise%20be%20clearing%20forest%20for%20cattle%20or%20short-lived%20crops%20like%20banana%20or%20cassava.%20Oil%20palm%2C%20as%20he%20rightly%20noted%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2077-0472%2F14%2F7%2F1133%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20sequester%20more%20carbon%20than%20such%20annual%20crops%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20studies%20have%20found%20it%20absorbs%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D6a614b02798915df929a998eb0260fe85575d32f30e0085841c1a786f39891cf%26postID%3D6758d4c6b942454853528030%26postSlug%3Dus-investors-and-the-destruction-of-peru-rainforest-2024-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41467-018-04755-y%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20less%20than%20half%20that%20of%20a%20standing%20forest%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20permanent%20crop%20that's%20going%20to%20grow%20for%20decades%20and%20decades%20and%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20it%20that%20people%20are%20going%20to%20do%20here%20in%20the%20jungle%3F%26quot%3B%20Doldourov%20asked.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20going%20to%20grow%20coca.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Spoor's%20view%2C%20only%20sustained%20investment%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20cultivation%20of%20valuable%20crops%20like%20oil%20palm%20on%20all%20the%20degraded%20land%20we%20had%20passed.%20If%20not%2C%20he%20said%2C%20settlers%20will%20keep%20clearing%20primary%20forest%20and%20abandoning%20the%20spent%20land%20a%20few%20years%20later.%20Fighting%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.abm9267%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emigratory%20agriculture%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20one%20of%20the%20goals%20of%20Peru's%20National%20Plan%20to%20Promote%20Oil%20Palm%2C%20enacted%20in%202000%2C%20which%20helped%20attract%20the%20company's%20investors%20to%20the%20region%20over%20a%20decade%20ago.%20%26quot%3BThose%20plantations%2C%2020%20years%20from%20now%2C%20will%20be%20the%20greenest%20areas%20in%20the%20whole%20zone%2C%26quot%3B%20Spoor%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20going%20to%20look%20back%20and%20go%2C%20'Wow%2C%20look%20at%20those%20two%20islands%20of%20green!'%20and%2C%20in%20some%20weird%20way%2C%20that%20will%20have%20been%20the%20result%20of%20what%20we%20started.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20dig%20deeper%20into%20the%20origins%20of%20Ocho%20Sur's%20plantations%2C%20I%20flew%20north%20to%20the%20jungle%20city%20of%20Iquitos%20to%20meet%20with%20William%20Park%2C%20a%20self-described%20%26quot%3Beco-social%20entrepreneur%26quot%3B%20from%20Bronxville%2C%20New%20York.%20Over%20an%20a%C3%A7ai%20bowl%20at%20the%20Dawn%20on%20the%20Amazon%20Caf%C3%A9%2C%20a%20favorite%20spot%20for%20travelers%20and%20expats%2C%20Park%20relayed%20his%20life%20story.%20He%20had%20served%20in%20the%20Marine%20Corps%20and%20earned%20a%20biology%20degree%20in%20college%2C%20but%20a%20childhood%20meeting%20with%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20organic%20food%20company%20Arrowhead%20Mills%20shaped%20his%20unconventional%20path.%20After%20a%20job%20running%20sales%20for%20a%20hemp%20apparel%20company%2C%20he%20lit%20out%20for%20Peru%2C%20where%20he%20launched%20Eco%20Ola%2C%20an%20export%20business%20in%20Amazonian%20superfoods%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20helping%20local%20communities%20develop%20sustainable%20economies%20from%20their%20native%20forests.%20Operating%20between%20two%20worlds%20%E2%80%94%20conservation%20and%20business%20%E2%80%94%20made%20him%20particularly%20suited%20to%20recognize%20what%20had%20unfolded%20here%20on%20the%20Amazon%20River%20back%20in%20June%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20Park%20was%20sitting%20on%20this%20same%20patio%20when%20he%20heard%20troubling%20news%20from%20a%20friend%20who%20lived%20upriver%20in%20Tamshiyacu%2C%20an%20isolated%20village%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20an%20uninterrupted%20swath%20of%20rainforest%20that%20stretched%20for%20hundreds%20of%20miles.%20The%20region%2C%20which%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20the%20world's%20greatest%20concentration%20of%20uncontacted%20Indigenous%20groups%2C%20is%20also%20home%20to%20several%20threatened%20species%2C%20including%20the%20bald-headed%20uakari%20monkey.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20vitally%20important%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20Park%20said.%20Now%2C%20according%20to%20Park's%20friend%2C%20a%20massive%20palm%20oil%20plantation%20was%20springing%20up%20in%20the%20area.%20Workers%20had%20been%20conducting%20surveys%20and%20slashing%20paths%20with%20machetes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20of%20Ocho%20Sur%20oil%20palm%20plantation%20worker%20and%20processing%20machine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67630af15cddac6581d6b148%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221389%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOil%20palm%20fruits%20being%20processed%20at%20Ocho%20Sur's%20mill%20in%20Ucayali.%20Every%2010%20days%2C%20each%20tree%20develops%20a%2050-pound%20cluster%20of%20fruits%20oozing%20with%20thick%2C%20red%20oil.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Park%20was%20skeptical.%20He%20often%20heard%20rumors%20of%20new%20megaprojects%2C%20but%20they%20usually%20fell%20apart%20before%20they%20got%20off%20the%20ground%20or%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20scams.%20Tamshiyacu%20seemed%20too%20remote%20to%20be%20worth%20anyone's%20while%2C%20he%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20wrong.%20Before%20long%2C%20workers%20showed%20up%20there%20with%20two%20dozen%20bulldozers%20and%20excavators.%20They%20proceeded%20east%2C%20widening%20and%20grading%20a%20dirt%20road%20for%20some%206%20miles%20until%20they%20reached%20their%20destination.%20%26quot%3BClearcutting%20happening%20now%2C%20the%20neighboring%20communities%20are%20not%20happy%2C%26quot%3B%20Park%20wrote%20to%20an%20environmentalist%20he%20knew.%20%26quot%3BThe%20name%20of%20the%20company%20and%20its%20international%20affiliations%20are%20not%20known%20but%20it%20is%20rumored%20to%20be%20a%20Malaysian%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20email%20eventually%20landed%20in%20the%20inbox%20of%20Matt%20Finer%2C%20a%20scientist%20then%20with%20the%20Center%20for%20International%20Environmental%20Law%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20Finer%20hunted%20for%20satellite%20images%20to%20confirm%20the%20devastation%2C%20while%20other%20environmentalists%20followed%20a%20paper%20trail%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20was%20behind%20the%20operation.%20Julia%20Urrunaga%2C%20who%20works%20as%20a%20researcher%20with%20the%20Environmental%20Investigation%20Agency%20tracking%20deforestation%20in%20the%20region%2C%20discovered%20a%20network%20of%20companies%20recently%20registered%20in%20the%20region.%20First%2C%20she%20found%20%26quot%3BPlantaciones%20de%20Loreto%26quot%3B%20based%20in%20Iquitos%2C%20then%20%26quot%3BPlantaciones%20de%20Ucayali.%26quot%3B%20Ultimately%2C%20she%20unearthed%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20interrelated%20companies.%20Like%20a%20series%20of%20nesting%20dolls%2C%20six%20of%20these%20companies%20were%20owned%20by%20two%20shell%20companies%20in%20the%20British%20Virgin%20Islands%2C%20which%20were%20in%20turn%20owned%20by%20a%20Cayman%20Islands-based%20company%20called%20United%20Oils%20Limited.%20This%20corporate%20labyrinth%20obscured%20the%20true%20shareholders%20and%20decision-makers%2C%20but%20one%20figure%20stood%20out%20in%20the%20records%3A%20Dennis%20Melka.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Worker%20at%20Ocho%20Sur%20oil%20palm%20plantation%2C%20Ucayali%2C%20Peru.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762ec8b0a6d56a4f9c1cd01%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20worker%20harvest%20palm%20fruits%20at%20the%20Tibecocha%20plantation.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20business%20records%20Urrunaga%20obtained%20and%20recently%20shared%20with%20me%2C%20Melka%20is%20the%20only%20one%20authorized%20by%20each%20of%20these%20entities%20to%20approve%20payments%20for%20%26quot%3Ban%20unlimited%20amount.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelka%2C%20Urrunaga%20learned%2C%20was%20a%20venture%20capitalist%20who%20had%20made%20his%20name%20developing%20palm%20oil%20plantations%20on%20Borneo%2C%20but%20she%20couldn't%20find%20much%20detail%20about%20his%20plans%20for%20Peru%2C%20or%20even%20what%20crops%20he%20planned%20to%20grow.%20Images%20online%20showed%20a%20sharply%20dressed%20man%20in%20his%20late%2030s%20with%20a%20bald%20head%20and%20blue%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiner%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20got%20his%20hands%20on%20the%20first%20clear%20satellite%20images%20showing%20strips%20of%20bare%2C%20red%20earth%20in%20the%20forest%20as%20the%20Tamshiyacu%20plantation%20took%20shape.%20Finer%20notified%20a%20journalist%20at%20the%20local%20newspaper%2C%20La%20Regi%C3%B3n%2C%20and%20a%20photograph%20of%20the%20naked%20landscape%20ended%20up%20on%20the%20front%20page.%20%26quot%3BWhere%20is%20the%20environmental%20prosecutor%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20paper%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20didn't%20yet%20know%20that%20Melka's%20clearing%20and%20planting%20was%20already%20further%20along%20in%20Ucayali.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20heard%20about%20Melka's%20role%20in%20these%20events%20some%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20talk%20to%20him%20in%20person%20at%20a%20conference%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20He%20was%20in%20his%20element%2C%20pitching%20investors%2C%20and%20looked%20relaxed%20in%20jeans%20and%20a%20blazer%20as%20he%20handed%20me%20his%20business%20card%20in%20a%20hotel%20banquet%20hall.%20He%20would%20be%20flying%20to%20Peru%20a%20few%20days%20later.%20When%20I%20started%20to%20ask%20about%20the%20deforestation%20allegations%20against%20him%2C%20his%20face%20grew%20tense%2C%20and%20he%20waved%20me%20away.%20%26quot%3BI%20created%20thousands%20of%20jobs%20in%20Peru%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BLeave%20me%20alone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20what%20I%20learned%20without%20his%20cooperation%2C%20Melka%20grew%20up%20in%20Marin%20County%2C%20California%2C%20and%20his%20first%20job%20out%20of%20college%20was%20at%20Credit%20Suisse%20in%20New%20York.%20After%20postings%20in%20London%20and%20Prague%2C%20he%20found%20his%20niche%20in%20the%20free-market%20mecca%20of%20Singapore%2C%20where%20he%20set%20up%20his%20own%20venture%20capital%20fund%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20those%20days%2C%20palm%20oil%20was%20booming%20on%20Borneo%2C%20a%2090-minute%20flight%20to%20the%20east.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20started%20meeting%20the%20companies%20and%20talking%20to%20them%2C%20I%20realized%20this%20was%20a%20phenomenal%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Melka%20later%20told%20a%20Singaporean%20publication.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20something%20I%20want%20to%20get%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20biggest%20problem%20was%20that%20most%20available%20land%20on%20Borneo%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20Indonesia%20and%20Malaysia%20was%20controlled%20by%20Indigenous%20people%20or%20held%20in%20state%20forestry%20concessions.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20special%20connections%20within%20the%20government%2C%20you%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20secure%20this%20land%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20Melka%20employee%20told%20me.%20Melka%20soon%20made%20those%20connections%20through%20a%20business%20partner%2C%20Graeme%20Iain%20Brown%2C%20whose%20father-in-law%2C%20according%20to%20an%20industry%20report%2C%20was%20a%20former%20Indonesian%20cabinet%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20Melka%20and%20his%20partners%20founded%20a%20company%20called%20Asian%20Plantations%20that%20obtained%2050%2C000%20acres%20of%20rainforest%20through%20what%20the%20company%20called%20%26quot%3Bnon-competitive%26quot%3B%20negotiations%20based%20on%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proactiveinvestors.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2F9059%2F-asian-plantations-acquires-5850-hectare-palm-oil-plantation-for-124-million-11390.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong%20standing%20local%20relationships.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20They%20proceeded%20to%20clear-cut%20their%20land%20and%20plant%20oil%20palm%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feia.org%2Freport%2Fdeforestation-by-definition%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esatellite%20analyses%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20the%20Environmental%20Investigation%20Agency.%20Six%20years%20later%2C%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Roundtable%20on%20Sustainable%20Palm%20Oil%2C%20they%20sold%20that%20operation%20to%20Felda%20Global%20Ventures%2C%20the%20third-largest%20palm%20oil%20company%20in%20the%20world%2C%20for%20almost%20%24200%20million.%20(Brown%20told%20me%20the%20notions%20that%20they%20had%20deforested%20any%20land%20or%20benefitted%20from%20family%20connections%20were%20%26quot%3Btotally%20false.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMalaysia%20and%20Indonesia%20dominated%20global%20palm%20oil%20production%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20usable%20land%20was%20predicted%20to%20run%20out%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade%20and%20Melka%20was%20already%20on%20the%20hunt%20for%20new%20territory.%20Company%20emails%20show%20that%20he%20reached%20out%20to%20government%20officials%20in%20the%20newly%20created%20country%20of%20South%20Sudan%20and%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20which%20was%20just%20opening%20for%20business%20after%20emerging%20from%20a%20military%20dictatorship.%20But%20Peru%20topped%20his%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20President%20Alan%20Garc%C3%ADa%2C%20Peru%20was%20welcoming%20foreign%20investors%20with%20open%20arms.%20Not%20only%20was%20Garc%C3%ADa's%20government%20offering%20sweetheart%20deals%20to%20foreign%20investors%20under%20its%20National%20Plan%20to%20Promote%20Oil%20Palm%2C%20but%20the%20country%20had%20more%20than%203%20million%20acres%20suitable%20for%20oil%20palm.%20%26quot%3BTax%20free%20at%20all%20levels!%26quot%3B%20Melka%20raved%20in%20an%20email%20to%20a%20London-based%20investment%20advisor.%20%26quot%3BLabor%20costs%20at%20US%2411.50%20per%20day.%20.%20.%20!%26quot%3B%20And%2C%20unlike%20in%20much%20of%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20Peru%20allowed%20foreigners%20to%20own%20plantations%20outright.%20Palm%20oil%2C%20as%20he%20put%20it%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2011-08-19%2Fasian-agri-seeks-100-million-for-palm-oil-fund-as-malaysia-land-runs-out%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20pitch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20profitable%20crop%20that%20humans%20can%20grow%20outside%20of%20narcotics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20more%20than%20a%20clever%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%2030%20years%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20palm%20oil%20industry%20in%20Peru%20has%20been%20directly%20stimulated%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20and%20by%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%2C%20which%20has%20spent%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20there%20funding%20organizations%20that%20work%20to%20redirect%20coca%20farmers%20toward%20alternative%20crops.%20The%20first%20oil%20palm%20project%2C%20spearheaded%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Office%20on%20Drugs%20and%20Crime%20in%201991%2C%20helped%20270%20families%20in%20Ucayali%20%E2%80%94%20largely%20refugees%20fleeing%20Shining%20Path%20guerillas%20%E2%80%94%20to%20establish%203%2C000%20acres%20of%20oil%20palm%20along%20a%20highway%20near%20Pucallpa.%20The%20United%20States%20later%20financed%20a%20mill%20that%20would%20be%20run%20by%20a%20farmer%20cooperative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20of%20indigenous%20palm%20oil%20worker%20at%20and%20him%20holding%20palm%20oil%20seeds%20at%20Shambo%20Porvenir%2C%20Ucayali%2C%20Peru.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67630e4d5cddac6581d6b275%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221431%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBruno%20Tangoa%2C%20chief%20of%20the%20Shambo%20Porvenir%20indigenous%20community%20in%20the%20Ucayali%20region%2C%20who%20grow%20palm%20oil%20for%20Ocho%20Sur%20on%20their%20land.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERolf%20Wachholtz%2C%20an%20economist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unodc.org%2Fdocuments%2Fevaluation%2FProEvals-2009%2FProEvals-2010%2FProEvals-2011%2FPER_D06_Evaluation_Report_Final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehired%20to%20evaluate%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20of%20the%20UN's%20coca-eradication%20programs%20in%202010%2C%20praised%20it%20for%20improving%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20farmers%20but%20stressed%20that%20the%20UN%20needed%20to%20%26quot%3Bfocus%20more%20on%20environmental%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20deforestation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelka%20worked%20to%20take%20full%20advantage%20of%20the%20government%20aid.%20After%20making%20connections%20with%20diplomats%20and%20development%20agencies%20in%20multiple%20countries%2C%20he%20was%20even%20hired%20by%20USAID%20to%20provide%20a%20financier's%20perspective%20on%20its%20work%20in%20Peru.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Peruvian%20industry%20needs%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20draft%20report%20he%20prepared%20in%202010.%20%26quot%3BAll%20UN%20%26amp%3B%20USAID%20efforts%20should%20be%20focused%20on%20growing%20the%20productive%20resource%20and%20planting%20land.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20November%2C%20he%20repeated%20the%20theme%20when%20he%20gave%20a%20talk%20in%20Lima%20organized%20by%20the%20UN%2C%20along%20with%20his%20business%20partner%20Bill%20Randall%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Pacific%20Agri%20Capital%2C%20a%20private%20equity%20firm%20that%20Melka%20founded%20in%202008%20to%20fund%20his%20Malaysian%20plantations.%20Peru%20still%20had%20only%20100%2C000%20acres%20of%20palm%20under%20cultivation%2C%20and%20Melka%20was%20seeking%20to%20triple%20that%20number%2C%20according%20to%20a%20documentary%20film%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zeit.de%2F2016%2F38%2Fperu-kokain-drogen-un-hans-jochen-wiese%2Fkomplettansicht%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20King%20of%20Cocaland%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BHe%20could%20impress%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wachholtz%2C%20the%20UN%20evaluator%2C%20who%20was%20in%20the%20audience%20that%20day.%20%26quot%3BI%20found%20it%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20Melka%20established%20the%20first%20eight%20Peruvian%20corporations%20for%20the%20plantations%20he%20wanted%20to%20develop%20%E2%80%94%20several%20of%20which%2C%20according%20to%20company%20records%2C%20would%20be%20acquired%20by%20his%20offshore%20holding%20company%2C%20United%20Oils.%20In%20a%20letter%20to%20local%20authorities%2C%20he%20wrote%20that%20his%20company%20had%20%26quot%3Bextensive%20experience%20implementing%20the%20world's%20best%20practices%20for%20environmental%20stewardship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20meeting%20at%20the%20US%20Embassy%20in%20Lima%2C%20Melka%20was%20introduced%20to%20Alfredo%20Rivera%20Loarte%2C%20an%20agronomist%20at%20the%20UN%20Office%20on%20Drugs%20and%20Crime.%20Melka%20promptly%20hired%20him%20as%20a%20consultant%20to%20oversee%20plantation%20operations.%20Rivera's%20son%20Julio%20also%20came%20on%20board%2C%20as%20did%20another%20UN%20employee%2C%20Maria%20Teresa%20Trigoso.%20Doldourov%2C%20who%20drove%20Spoor%20and%20me%20around%20during%20my%20visit%2C%20had%20also%20worked%20at%20the%20UN%2C%20and%20built%20roads%20for%20United%20Oils%20before%20joining%20Ocho%20Sur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20United%20Oils%2C%20Melka%20created%20United%20Cacao%2C%20having%20decided%20that%20the%20Tamshiyacu%20plantation%20to%20the%20north%20was%20better%20suited%20for%20that%20crop.%20Melka%20boasted%20of%20his%20UN%20ties%20every%20chance%20he%20got%2C%20writing%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unitedcacao.com%2Findex.php%2Fen%2Fcorporate-profile-eng%2Fbusiness-description%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20pitch%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20his%20senior%20managers%20collectively%20had%20several%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20three%20years%2C%20Melka%20raised%20%2438%20million%20for%20United%20Oils%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company's%20shareholder%20records.%20Seed%20funds%20came%20from%20wealthy%20friends%20and%20friends%20of%20friends%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20told%20me%20they%20hadn't%20fully%20appreciated%20what%20they%20were%20supporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%20I%20had%20started%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20orangutans%20and%20how%20they%20were%20being%20impacted%20by%20palm%20oil%20plantations%26quot%3B%20on%20Borneo%2C%20said%20one%20American%20investor%2C%20who%20was%20so%20ashamed%20by%20his%20participation%20that%20he%20asked%20me%20to%20withhold%20his%20name.%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20fuck%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20remembered%20thinking.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20put%20my%20money%20with%20someone%20who%20is%20clearing%20forest%20in%20the%20Amazon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelka%20quickly%20lined%20up%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20investors.%20Early%20financers%20included%20Eric%20Varvel%2C%20then%20the%20CEO%20of%20Credit%20Suisse%20in%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20region%20and%20Steadfast%20Financial%2C%20a%20New%20York%20hedge%20fund%20with%20over%20%248%20billion%20under%20management.%20At%20the%20company's%20launch%2C%20the%20majority%20shareholder%2C%20with%20%2410%20million%20in%20equity%2C%20was%20a%20fund%20managed%20by%20Randall%20at%20Pacific%20Agri%20Capital.%20Randall's%20fund%20received%20%243%20million%20in%20capital%20from%20Anholt%20Services%2C%20a%20holding%20company%20that%20managed%20the%20%242%20billion%20trust%20left%20behind%20by%20the%20Danish%20petroleum%20shipping%20magnate%20Torben%20Karlshoej%2C%20who%20founded%20Teekay.%20Though%20Anholt%20was%20an%20indirect%20investor%20in%20United%20Oils%2C%20the%20company%20received%20a%20privileged%20view%20of%20the%20company's%20inner%20workings%20directly%20from%20Melka%2C%20according%20to%20a%20confidentiality%20agreement%20signed%20in%20September%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20after%20being%20assured%20by%20local%20counsel%20that%20Melka%20was%20complying%20with%20Peruvian%20laws%2C%20Anholt%20joined%20with%20a%20core%20group%20of%20shareholders%20in%20providing%20United%20Oils%20with%20an%20additional%20%2448%20million%20through%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconvoca.pe%2Finvestigacion%2Fmelka-case-financiers-behind-oil-palm-business-amazonian-deforested-areas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate%20bond%20offering%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20business%20can%20support%20easily%20US%2450m%20in%20debt%20or%20so%20(or%20more)%2C%26quot%3B%20Melka%20assured%20a%20shareholder%20in%20an%20email.%20He%20had%20purchased%20%247%20million%20of%20the%20company's%20debt%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelka%20told%20his%20shareholders%20that%20he%20was%20aiming%20for%20an%20initial%20public%20offering%20on%20either%20the%20Nasdaq%20or%20the%20London%20Stock%20Exchange%20in%20early%202016.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20meeting%20with%20mid-tier%20investment%20banks%20with%20positive%20feedback%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BGranted%20i-banks%20will%20always%20whisper%20'sweet%20nothings'%20in%20a%20client's%20ear%20but%20at%20least%20there%20is%20interest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20challenge%20was%20acquiring%20land%20for%20the%20plantations.%20Outside%20conservation%20areas%20and%20Indigenous%20communities%2C%20much%20of%20the%20Peruvian%20Amazon%20was%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20regional%20governments%3A%20Undivided%2C%20untitled%2C%20and%20unclaimed%2C%20it%20was%20controlled%20by%20a%20glacial%20bureaucracy%20in%20a%20country%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F01%2F25%2Fperu-protests-political-crisis-castillo-boluarte-corruption%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20corruption%20was%20widespread%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20fresh%20infusion%20of%20cash%2C%20Melka%20needed%20to%20either%20find%20large%20blocks%20of%20land%20that%20cash-strapped%20authorities%20in%20Ucayali%20were%20willing%20to%20swiftly%20title%20and%20sell%20to%20him%20directly%2C%20or%20buy%20individual%20properties%20from%20homesteaders%20%E2%80%94%20settlers%20who%20had%20obtained%20%26quot%3Bcertificates%20of%20possession%26quot%3B%20for%20untitled%20state%20lands%20by%20proving%20they%20had%20used%20it%20continuously%20for%20at%20least%20one%20year.%20According%20to%20Juan%20Luis%20Dammert%20Bello%2C%20a%20Peruvian%20geographer%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20growth%20of%20plantations%20in%20the%20Amazon%2C%20buying%20land%20from%20settlers%20is%20an%20attractive%20loophole%20for%20large%20developers%20who%20are%20restricted%20from%20clearing%20forest%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wilson%20Barbaran%20in%20a%20shed%20with%20a%20thatch%20roof%20and%20a%20hammoc%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67631a1f0a6d56a4f9c1e5c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWilson%20Barbar%C3%A1n%20Soria%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Santa%20Clara%20indigenous%20community.%20After%20his%20election%20in%202022%2C%20he%20asked%20prosecutors%20to%20withdraw%20the%20community%20as%20a%20party%20to%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20Ocho%20Sur.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20shady%20intermediaries%20known%20as%20land%20traffickers%20were%20organizing%20peasants%20to%20invade%20untitled%20lands%20and%20then%20packaging%20and%20selling%20the%20properties%20for%20a%20profit.%20Sometimes%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bsettlers%26quot%3B%20they%20enlisted%20never%20actually%20set%20foot%20on%20the%20land%20they%20were%20claiming%3A%20They%20just%20signed%20a%20document%20asserting%20that%20they%20had.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconvoca.pe%2Finvestigacion%2Famazonia-el-negocio-de-tierras-deforestadas-en-los-dominios-del-poderoso-grupo-romero%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELand-trafficking%20mafias%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20operate%20in%20every%20region%20of%20Peru%2C%20have%20allowed%20developers%20to%20launder%20unclaimed%20swaths%20of%20rainforest%20into%20legal%20farmland.%20But%20experts%20say%20Melka's%20enablers%20would%20be%20the%20first%20to%20carry%20it%20out%20on%20such%20a%20large%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMelka%20is%20the%20game%20changer%2C%26quot%3B%20Dammert%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20before%20and%20an%20after.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelka%20used%20his%20UN%20ties%20to%20identify%20promising%20opportunities%2C%20according%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20King%20of%20Cocaland%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20documentary%20film%20about%20Hans-Jochen%20Wiese%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20UN's%20alternative%20development%20program%20in%20Peru.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20supposed%20to%20designate%20land%20suitable%20for%20growing%20oil%20palms%2C%26quot%3B%20Pablo%20Ram%C3%ADrez%20Mori%2C%20an%20official%20with%20the%20regional%20agriculture%20authority%20in%20Ucayali%20told%20the%20filmmakers.%20Wiese%2C%20Ram%C3%ADrez%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bagreed%20to%20this%20or%20that%20zone.%26quot%3B%20Ram%C3%ADrez%20declined%20my%20request%20for%20an%20interview%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bup%20to%20the%20authorities%20to%20follow%20the%20process%26quot%3B%3B%20Wiese%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gacetaucayalina.com%2F2023%2F04%2Ffallece-hans-jochen-friedrich-wiese-investigador-y-principal-promotor-del-cultivo-de-palma-aceitera-.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20died%20in%20an%20accident%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20had%20said%20his%20only%20goal%20in%20helping%20Melka%20was%20to%20help%20the%20Peruvian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20Melka%20acquired%20the%2017%2C000-acre%20Tibecocha%20property%2C%20which%20included%20222%20parcels%20owned%20by%20an%20association%20of%20farmers.%20The%20association's%20members%20had%20obtained%20certificates%20of%20possession%20years%20earlier%20under%20questionable%20circumstances%2C%20according%20to%20Dammert's%20research.%20Apart%20from%20the%20extraction%20of%20high-value%20timber%2C%20Peruvian%20auditors%20found%20little%20evidence%20that%20they%20had%20cultivated%20it%20in%20a%20sustained%20way%20during%20their%20tenure%2C%20as%20required%20under%20the%20law.%20Most%20of%20them%20didn't%20even%20live%20nearby.%20Dammert%20has%20called%20it%20a%20textbook%20example%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proquest.com%2Fopenview%2F3f8ef5d5c957bb298e99ea9a5fece9d1%2F1%3Fpq-origsite%3Dgscholar%26cbl%3D18750%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eghost%20titling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20government%20officials%20create%20an%20association%20whose%20ranks%20they%20fill%20primarily%20with%20friends%20and%20relatives%2C%20hoping%20to%20profit%20from%20a%20subsequent%20sale.%20One%20sales%20contract%2C%20for%20a%20109-acre%20parcel%2C%20indicates%20that%20Melka%20paid%20members%20of%20the%20group%20about%20%24100%20an%20acre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Updated%20Ocho%20Sur%20U%20Edit%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2F7m4Wu7Gd-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2010%20miles%20west%20of%20Tibecocha%2C%20Melka%20obtained%20a%20second%20property%2C%20Zanja%20Seca%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proetica.org.pe%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2Fthe-business-of-deforestation.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eby%20different%20means%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20included%2011%2C000%20acres%20of%20state%20land%20in%20Ucayali%20that%20had%20already%20been%20surveyed%20and%20would%20soon%20be%20mass-titled%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20support%20a%20hundred%20or%20so%20subsistence%20farmers%20who%20had%20abandoned%20coca%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fissuu.com%2Fimpetu%2Fdocs%2Fimpetu_08_de_mayo_del_2018%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20a%20USAID-funded%20program%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20soon%20as%20they%20received%20their%20certificates%20of%20possession%2C%20these%20farmers%20were%20hoping%20to%20plant%20cacao%20and%20oil%20palm.%20But%20after%20a%20massive%20fiscal%20decentralization%2C%20the%20Ucayali%20government%20was%20in%20need%20of%20cash.%20Ucayali%20authorities%20began%20dragging%20their%20feet%20in%20finalizing%20the%20homesteading%20paperwork%2C%20according%20to%20a%20legal%20complaint%20filed%20by%20the%20farmers.%20Then%2C%20to%20their%20great%20surprise%2C%20Melka%20purchased%20all%2011%2C000%20acres%20directly%20from%20the%20state%20for%20a%20steal%3A%20%2425%20an%20acre.%20(This%20month%2C%20three%20officials%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gob.pe%2Finstitucion%2Fcsjucayali%2Fnoticias%2F1082130-condenan-a-exfuncionarios-de-agricultura-por-negociacion-incompatible-en-caso-zanja-seca%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esentenced%20to%20prison%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20an%20anti-corruption%20court%20for%20abuse%20of%20their%20positions%20in%20making%20that%20deal.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20lands%20in%20hand%2C%20Melka%20hired%20contractors%20to%20bulldoze%20the%20forest%2C%20burying%20the%20trees%20in%20trenches%20to%20improve%20the%20poor%20tropical%20soil.%20Analyses%20of%20satellite%20images%20conducted%20by%20the%20Peruvian%20government%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maaproject.org%2F2015%2Fimage-4-oil-palm-projects-cause-deforestation-of-primary-forest-in-the-peruvian-amazon-part-1-nueva-requena%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicate%20that%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20Zanja%20Seca%20and%20Tibecocha%20properties%20were%20covered%20with%20primary%20or%20secondary%20forest%20at%20the%20time%20Melka%20took%20ownership.%20A%20million%20palm%20seeds%20were%20soon%20imported%20from%20Ecuador%2C%20Colombia%2C%20Costa%20Rica%2C%20and%20Ivory%20Coast.%20Worker%20camps%2C%20dining%20areas%2C%20and%20soccer%20fields%20were%20erected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Melka's%20development%20of%20the%20plantations%20came%20new%20roads%2C%20followed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oicrf.org%2F-%2Fland-trafficking-agribusiness-titling-campaigns-and-deforestation-in-the-peruvian-amazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20homesteaders%2C%20speculators%2C%20and%20land%20traffickers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Dammert%20and%20other%20researchers.%20Oil%20palm%20spread%20in%20the%20uplands%2C%20rice%20crops%20in%20the%20peatlands.%20Land%20conflicts%20were%20on%20the%20rise.%20Melka's%20two%20plantations%20were%20like%20a%20tightening%20vise%2C%20forcing%20communities%20in%20the%20middle%20to%20decide%20whether%20they%20would%20work%20with%20the%20company%20or%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Landscape%20portrait%20of%20a%20Palm%20oil%20plantation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762eec26c531c315b88ed42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Tibecocha%20plantation%20stretches%20across%2017%2C000%20acres%20of%20what%20was%20once%20rainforest.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20communities%20trapped%20in%20this%20vise%20was%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya%2C%20an%20Indigenous%20Shipibo%20village%20tucked%20away%20in%20a%20looping%20bend%20of%20the%20Aguayt%C3%ADa%20River%2C%20a%20tributary%20of%20the%20Ucayali.%20The%20Peruvian%20state%20granted%20the%20community%20about%20540%20acres%20in%201986.%20It%20wasn't%20much%2C%20but%20they%20had%20only%20to%20cross%20the%20river%20to%20hunt%20wild%20game%2C%20gather%20native%20fruits%2C%20and%20harvest%20natural%20dyes%20for%20pottery%20and%20textiles%20they%20sold%20in%20local%20markets.%20Now%2C%20those%20forests%20were%20being%20cleared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20April%202015%20letter%20to%20the%20director%20of%20the%20regional%20agriculture%20authority%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya%20complained%20about%20their%20situation.%20%26quot%3BOur%20ancestral%20territory%20has%20been%20granted%20to%20Plantaciones%20de%20Pucallpa%20for%20the%20planting%20of%20oil%20palm%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20They%20requested%20a%20territorial%20expansion%20to%20make%20up%20for%20what%20was%20being%20lost.%20And%20to%20help%20their%20cause%20they%20summoned%20a%20prominent%20Indigenous%20activist%2C%20Washington%20Bol%C3%ADvar%20D%C3%ADaz%2C%20a%20descendant%20of%20the%20neighboring%20Kakataibo%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBol%C3%ADvar%20had%20helped%20found%20a%20federation%20uniting%20nine%20Kakataibo%20communities%20and%20became%20an%20eloquent%20defender%20of%20Indigenous%20rights.%20He%20was%20immediately%20recognizable%20by%20his%20long%20hair%20and%20the%20beaded%20necklaces%20and%20headdresses%20he%20wore%20for%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202015%2C%20Boliv%C3%A1r%20filed%20a%20legal%20complaint%20with%20Peru's%20Public%20Ministry%2C%20which%20has%20the%20power%20to%20launch%20criminal%20investigations.%20In%20it%2C%20he%20alleged%20that%20corrupt%20officials%20in%20the%20regional%20agriculture%20department%20had%20conspired%20with%20Melka's%20company%20to%20steal%20and%20deforest%20their%20lands.%20He%20described%20visiting%20the%20Tibecocha%20property%20one%20morning%20that%20month%20with%20a%20contingent%20from%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya%20as%20part%20of%20a%20government%20inspection.%20Bol%C3%ADvar%20said%20he%20was%20shocked%20to%20hear%20%26quot%3Bcrying%20baby%20monkeys%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bwounded%20animals%20looking%20for%20their%20mothers%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20sun%20beat%20down%20on%20a%20landscape%20that%20had%20become%20%26quot%3Ba%20cemetery%20of%20trees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222528%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gustavo%20Hoyos%20with%20his%20pet%20monkey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762ea510a6d56a4f9c1cc34%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221685%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGustavo%20Hoyos%20with%20a%20pet%20monkey%20in%20the%20indigenous%20community%20of%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMelka%20tended%20to%20move%20fast%2C%20and%20that%20held%20true%20as%20he%20snapped%20up%20land.%20A%20new%2C%20stricter%20agricultural%20law%20had%20gone%20into%20force%20in%20Peru%20in%202012%2C%20but%20he%20didn't%20wait%20for%20the%20government's%20sign-off%20on%20an%20environmental%20management%20plan%20or%20obtain%20a%20%26quot%3Bchange%20of%20use%26quot%3B%20authorization%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20property's%20suitability%20for%20growing%20crops%2C%20according%20to%20a%202022%20audit%20by%20Peru's%20comptroller%20general.%20Nor%20did%20he%20leave%2030%25%20of%20the%20property's%20forest%20cover%20intact%2C%20as%20required%20under%20the%20law%2C%20the%20audit%20found.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20audit%20said%2C%20Melka%20had%20cleared%20property%20he%20did%20not%20even%20own%2C%20including%20several%20hundred%20acres%20of%20a%20state-owned%20timberland%20known%20as%20the%20Biabo%20Cordillera%20Azul%2C%20which%20abutted%20the%20Tibecocha%20lands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20that%20corner-cutting%20stopped%20Melka%20from%20working%20toward%20his%20dream%20of%20earning%20environmental%20plaudits%20for%20his%20palm%20oil.%20In%20October%202013%2C%20a%20United%20Oils%20subsidiary%2C%20Plantaciones%20de%20Pucallpa%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frspo.my.site.com%2FComplaint%2Fs%2Fcase%2F50090000028Es1LAAS%2Fdetail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoined%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Roundtable%20on%20Sustainable%20Palm%20Oil.%20Becoming%20a%20member%20was%20the%20first%20step%20toward%20getting%20the%20farm%20certified%20as%20100%25%20sustainable%2C%20which%20could%20mean%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwwfint.awsassets.panda.org%2Fdownloads%2Fexecutive_summary_.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202%25%20to%207%25%20premium%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20US%20and%20European%20markets.%20According%20to%20roundtable%20records%2C%20Melka's%20subsidiary%20affirmed%20that%20it%20had%20not%20cleared%20any%20forest%20for%20Tibecocha.%20Melka%20prepared%20for%20certification%20by%20commissioning%20an%20art-deco-style%20poster%20showing%20a%20worker%20hoisting%20a%20palm%20seedling%20in%20front%20of%20a%20pale%20yellow%20sun.%20%26quot%3BUnited%20Oils%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reads.%20%26quot%3BWorld's%20Finest%20Palm%20Oil.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20investigators%20were%20now%20fanning%20out%20across%20Ucayali%20to%20interview%20hundreds%20of%20suspects%20and%20witnesses%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20criminal%20investigation%20that%20Bol%C3%ADvar's%20complaint%20set%20off.%20They%20soon%20discovered%20Melka%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20pulling%20off%20his%20most%20brazen%20scheme.%20To%20skirt%20the%20reputational%20risks%20of%20buying%20more%20land%20directly%2C%20his%20employees%20had%20begun%20selecting%20parcels%20for%20homesteaders%20to%20clear%20themselves%2C%20then%20lending%20them%20money%20for%20fertilizer%20and%20seedlings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20would%20effectively%20become%20contract%20farmers%20for%20United%20Oils%20%E2%80%94%20in%20debt%20to%20the%20company%20from%20the%20moment%20they%20set%20foot%20on%20their%20new%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelka's%20team%20had%20pitched%20the%20idea%20directly%20to%20farmers.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20oil%20palm%3F%20Where%20will%20it%20take%20us%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20sons%20of%20Alfredo%20Rivera%2C%20the%20manager%20Melka%20hired%20after%20his%20decades%20with%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20told%20a%20group%20gathered%20near%20Zanja%20Seca%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Fjournals%2Fforests-and-global-change%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Fffgc.2019.00014%2Ffull%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20transcript%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20researcher%20who%20attended%20the%20meeting.%20%26quot%3BLook%2C%20how%20I%20have%20credit%20cards%20like%20a%20casino!%20One%20for%20my%20wife%2C%20one%20for%20me%2C%20another%20one%20for%20my%20wife%2C%20and%20another%20one%20for%20me.%20That%20is%20what%20oil%20palm%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20farmers'%20paperwork%20would%20get%20fast-tracked%20by%20the%20regional%20agriculture%20director%2C%20a%20man%20named%20Isaac%20Huam%C3%A1n%20P%C3%A9rez%20who%20was%20a%20true%20believer%20in%20the%20promise%20of%20oil%20palm%20to%20alleviate%20poverty.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20alternatives%20do%20we%20have%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked%20me.%20Though%20he%20said%20he%20had%20never%20met%20Melka%2C%20he%20had%20longstanding%20ties%20to%20the%20United%20Oils%20team.%20He%20had%20known%20Alfredo%20Rivera%20since%20the%201990s.%20Huam%C3%A1n%20also%20told%20me%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20great%20friend%26quot%3B%20of%20Ulises%20Salda%C3%B1a%20Bardales%2C%20the%20former%20mayor%20of%20Pucallpa%20whom%20Melka%20had%20hired%20as%20institutional%20relations%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20the%20regional%20agricultural%20department%20of%20Ucayali%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67631f255cddac6581d6ba5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20office%20where%20Isaac%20Huam%C3%A1n%20P%C3%A9rez%2C%20Ucayali's%20regional%20agricultural%20director%2C%20fast-tracked%20the%20titling%20of%20lands%20that%20prosecutors%20say%20were%20destined%20for%20Dennis%20Melka's%20plantations.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20farmers%20who%20seized%20the%20opportunity%20was%20Freddy%20Monteluiz%20Paima%2C%20who%20lives%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20two%20children%20in%20the%20community%20of%20Esperanza%2C%20a%20village%20on%20the%20left%20bank%20of%20the%20Aguayt%C3%ADa.%20When%20I%20arrived%20at%20his%20wooden%20home%20one%20May%20afternoon%2C%20he%20told%20me%20that%20he%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20oil%20palm%20was%20until%20Melka's%20people%20arrived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20money%20sounded%20good%2C%20and%20he%20said%20he%20happily%20joined%2016%20other%20residents%20in%202015%20who%20heeded%20the%20company's%20call.%20They%20grabbed%20their%20chainsaws%20and%20piled%20onto%20several%20tuk%20tuks%2C%20heading%20out%20to%20a%20500-acre%20plot%20of%20land%20that%20a%20local%20land%20trafficker%20had%20told%20them%20they%20could%20claim%20as%20their%20own%20to%20cultivate%20oil%20palm%20for%20the%20company.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20where%20the%20conflict%20began%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelka%20had%20sought%20to%20bring%20another%2012%2C000%20acres%20into%20cultivation%20through%20this%20sharecropping%20strategy.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%20total%20of%20128%20certificates%20of%20possession%2C%20totaling%20at%20least%207%2C000%20acres%2C%20were%20rubber-stamped%20by%20the%20titling%20division%20overseen%20by%20Huam%C3%A1n%2C%20the%20regional%20agricultural%20director.%20Apart%20from%20Monteluiz%20and%20a%20few%20others%20from%20Esperanza%2C%20most%20of%20the%20other%20new%20landholders%20had%20no%20connection%20to%20the%20area%3B%20some%20went%20to%20relatives%20of%20Huam%C3%A1n%20or%20other%20officials%20in%20his%20office%2C%20according%20to%20a%20prosecutorial%20report%20I%20obtained.%20When%20Ucayali's%20field-titling%20team%20visited%20the%20area%20in%20September%202015%2C%20the%20settlers%20could%20not%20even%20point%20out%20their%20own%20parcels.%20The%20property%20lines%20had%20all%20been%20drawn%20in%20a%20back%20office%20in%20Pucallpa%2C%20signed%20off%20on%20by%20the%20town's%20mayor%2C%20who%20was%20working%20with%20the%20land%20trafficker.%20The%20process%20was%20so%20haphazard%20that%20some%20of%20the%20parcels%20Huam%C3%A1n%20approved%20were%20partway%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fes.mongabay.com%2F2018%2F12%2Ftrafico-tierras-ucayali-bosques-desaparecen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einside%20a%20lake%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20quickly%20backfired.%20On%20September%2024%2C%202015%2C%20according%20to%20prosecutors'%20records%20and%20interviews%20with%20participants%2C%20Bol%C3%ADvar%20and%20a%20few%20dozen%20residents%20of%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya%2C%20outfitted%20with%20rusty%20machetes%20and%20rifles%2C%20headed%20out%20to%20the%20disputed%20land%20to%20confront%20the%20settlers.%20Monteluiz%20and%20his%20companions%20fled%20into%20the%20jungle%2C%20leaving%20behind%20their%20chainsaws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%20Julia%20Urrunaga%2C%20of%20the%20Environmental%20Investigation%20Agency%2C%20had%20published%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feia.org%2Freport%2Fdeforestation-by-definition%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetailed%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Melka's%20modus%20operandi%20in%20Malaysian%20Borneo%20and%20Peru%2C%20arguing%20that%20a%20failure%20to%20prosecute%20him%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bto%20expose%20Peru's%20national%20forest%20patrimony%20to%20rampant%20illegality%20and%20ultimately%20deforestation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cost%20is%20simply%20too%20high%2C%20the%20victims%20too%20many%2C%20for%20Peru%20not%20to%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20and%20her%20colleagues%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20portrait%20of%20former%20community%20chief%20Mario%20Hoyos.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762e9206c531c315b88eb4b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20family%20home%20and%20shop%20in%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeruvian%20regulators%20had%20issued%20a%20stop-work%20order%20to%20the%20Zanja%20Seca%20plantation%20for%20failing%20to%20comply%20with%20environmental%20regulations%3B%20now%20they%20ordered%20work%20to%20halt%20on%20the%20Tibecocha%20plantation%20too.%20The%20Roundtable%20on%20Sustainable%20Palm%20Oil%20followed%20suit%20with%20its%20own%20stop-work%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20response%20to%20the%20roundtable%2C%20the%20company%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20these%20lands%20had%20been%20degraded%20by%20the%20illegal%20cultivation%20of%20coca%2C%20and%20by%20other%20exploitations%20of%20the%20forest%2C%20such%20as%20illegal%20timber%20and%20migratory%20cultivation%20over%2040%20years.%26quot%3B%20As%20for%20the%20growing%20international%20controversy%2C%20Melka%20responded%20by%20lashing%20out.%20In%20one%20unsigned%20email%20to%20a%20Czech%20journalist%2C%20he%20called%20Bol%C3%ADvar%20%26quot%3Ba%20total%20fraud%26quot%3B%20and%20warned%20the%20reporter%20to%20%26quot%3Bcease%20and%20desist%20from%20attacking%20our%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20over%20a%20year%2C%20Melka%20was%20able%20to%20defy%20the%20stop-work%20orders%20and%20operate%20without%20consequence.%20He%20could%20not%2C%20however%2C%20operate%20without%20capital.%20The%20first%20revenue%20from%20palm%20oil%20sales%20wouldn't%20arrive%20until%20the%20end%20of%202016%2C%20and%20he%20was%20so%20underfinanced%2C%20according%20to%20one%20investor%2C%20that%20he%20wasn't%20spending%20enough%20to%20adequately%20fertilize%20the%20trees.%20%26quot%3BBank%20accounts%20are%20empty%2C%26quot%3B%20Melka%20emailed%20his%20board.%20%26quot%3BSuppliers%20are%20physically%20protesting%20outside%20the%20office%20doors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20February%2C%20United%20Oils%20defaulted%20on%20a%20%245%20million%20interest%20payment%20on%20its%20corporate%20bonds.%20The%20%2448%20million%20principal%20would%20be%20due%20in%20six%20months%20time.%20Melka%20wrote%20his%20shareholders%20to%20say%20that%20his%20attempts%20to%20obtain%20bridge%20financing%20had%20gone%20nowhere.%20United%20Oils%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20insolvency%2C%20and%20Melka%20would%20soon%20be%20publicly%20named%20in%20a%20criminal%20investigation%20against%20the%20company%20and%20its%20collaborators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crisis%20pitted%20Melka's%20investors%20against%20one%20another.%20Some%20shareholders%20stood%20to%20gain%20in%20a%20bankruptcy%20and%20some%20stood%20to%20lose%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20much%20of%20the%20company's%20debt%20they%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20final%20balance%20sheet%2C%20dated%20March%202016%2C%20tallied%20the%20company's%20assets%20at%20%2477%20million.%20If%20a%20foreclosure%20auction%20reaped%20offers%20in%20that%20ballpark%2C%20the%20surplus%20could%20pay%20back%20most%20of%20what%20the%20shareholders%20had%20put%20in%2C%20and%20then%20some.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20debt%20trumps%20equity%2C%20and%20Anholt%2C%20the%20lead%20creditor%20with%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%20the%20debt%2C%20had%20oversight%20over%20any%20sale.%20That%20gave%20Bill%20Randall%20of%20Pacific%20Agri%20Capital%20grave%20concerns%3A%20Though%20Randall's%20funds%20had%20been%20pivotal%20in%20the%20company's%20early%20days%2C%20they%20had%20only%20purchased%206%25%20of%20the%20company's%20debt.%20Anholt%2C%20he%20warned%20in%20a%20May%2011%20memo%2C%20might%20try%20to%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20the%20price%20of%20the%20assets%20as%20low%20as%20possible%20and%20attract%20as%20little%20number%20of%20bidders%20for%20the%20assets%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Cayman%20Islands%20law%2C%20Anholt's%20lawyer%20wrote%20back%2C%20creditors%20had%20no%20obligation%20to%20achieve%20the%20highest%20possible%20price.%20As%20for%20Melka%2C%20company%20balance%20sheets%20show%20that%20his%20stake%20in%20the%20plantations%20would%20remain%20around%2015%25%20after%20a%20sale.%20(Randall%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment%2C%20and%20Anholt%20referred%20all%20questions%20about%20its%20investment%20to%20Spoor.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvertisements%20soon%20appeared%20in%20the%20pages%20of%20El%20Peruano%20and%20The%20Jakarta%20Post%20inviting%20interested%20bidders%20to%20participate%20in%20a%20public%20auction%20of%20the%20plantations.%20On%20the%20auction's%20final%20day%2C%20July%2014%2C%20Anholt%20and%20the%20other%20bondholders%20acquired%20all%20of%20United%20Oils'%20assets%20in%20exchange%20for%20forgiveness%20of%20their%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20company's%20name%3A%20Ocho%20Sur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20records%20indicate%20that%2018%20of%20the%2019%20shareholders%20in%20Ocho%20Sur%20funded%20entities%20that%20bankrolled%20Melka's%20work%20clearing%20and%20planting%20of%20the%20rainforest%20between%202012%20and%202014.%20With%20Melka%20and%20other%20key%20personnel%20from%20the%20early%20days%20remaining%20involved%2C%20the%20only%20truly%20new%20player%20was%20Amerra%20Capital%20Management%2C%20a%20New%20York%20private%20equity%20firm%20whose%20funds%20purchased%20%2410%20million%20of%20United%20Oils'%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Peruvian%20prosecutors%2C%20Amerra%20had%20been%20told%20in%20a%20due-diligence%20document%20that%20United%20Oils%20had%20%26quot%3Bcaused%20the%20deforestation%20of%20approximately%207%2C000%20hectares.%26quot%3B%20Amerra's%20managing%20partner%2C%20Craig%20Tashjian%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%2C%20but%20a%20person%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20portfolio%20told%20me%20the%20information%20they%20received%20on%20the%20legality%20of%20the%20plantations%20was%20inconclusive.%20%26quot%3BWe%20looked%20at%20this%20so%20many%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20the%20investors%20took%20it%20for%20granted%20that%20Melka%20was%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C3%81lvaro%20Rod%C3%A1s%20Farro%2C%20the%20prosecutor%20specializing%20in%20organized%20crime%20who%20named%20Ocho%20Sur%20in%20the%20case%20against%20Melka%2C%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20transfer%20of%20the%20mature%20plantations%20was%20part%20of%20a%20criminal%20conspiracy%20in%20which%20Melka%20was%20the%20ringleader.%20He%20dubbed%20the%20maneuver%20%26quot%3Bcovert%20business%20succession.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20robustly%20denied%20this%20claim.%20%26quot%3BOcho%20Sur%20is%20not%20the%20continuation%20of%20any%20previous%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20wrote%20in%20February%20in%20response%20to%20a%20new%20report%20from%20the%20Environmental%20Investigation%20Agency.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20incorrect%20and%20impossible%20to%20attribute%20to%20it%20any%20alleged%20actions%20that%20occurred%20before%20its%20existence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20tight-knit%20circle%20of%20environmentalists%20in%20Peru%20who%20had%20been%20tracking%20Melka%20for%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20they%20were%20in%20the%20dark%20during%20the%202016%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnless%20you%20had%20a%20budget%20for%20bodyguards%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Lucila%20Pautrat%20Oyarz%C3%BAn%2C%20the%20forest%20engineer%20who%20runs%20Ken%C3%A9%2C%20a%20tiny%20Peruvian%20environmental%20NGO%2C%20certainly%20didn't%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20too%20dangerous%20to%20travel%20to%20Pucallpa%20at%20that%20time.%20Since%202010%2C%20at%20least%2029%20environmental%20defenders%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20Peruvian%20Amazon.%20Pautrat%20instead%20monitored%20the%20situation%20from%20Lima%2C%20in%20a%20modest%20third-floor%20apartment%20where%20the%20shades%20were%20always%20drawn%2C%20messaging%20with%20government%20informants%20and%20managing%20undercover%20investigators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222071%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20of%20Lucila%20Pautrat%20and%20her%20pointing%20at%20some%20plans.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67630cac0a6d56a4f9c1e048%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22984%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEnvironmental%20activist%20Lucila%20Pautrat.%20Her%20organization%2C%20Ken%C3%A9%2C%20and%20other%20environmental%20NGOs%20have%20been%20attacked%20by%20the%20right%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcaviar%20mafia.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20January%202017%20that%20Pautrat%20first%20saw%20the%20name%20Ocho%20Sur%20in%20a%20document%20she%20obtained%20from%20the%20Peruvian%20business%20registry.%20Then%20she%20got%20a%20tip%20that%20Melka%20was%20still%20visiting%20Pucallpa%2C%20in%20his%20roles%20as%20a%20consultant%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20board.%20In%20fact%2C%20she%20learned%2C%20several%20key%20players%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Alfredo%20Rivera%2C%20Ulises%20Salda%C3%B1a%2C%20and%20Krassimir%20Doldorouv%20%E2%80%94%20continued%20working%20their%20old%20jobs%20for%20the%20new%20company.%20Ocho%20Sur%20kept%20the%20same%20United%20Oils%20offices%20in%20what%20would%20become%20the%20Wyndham%20hotel.%20The%20signs%20were%20simply%20updated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPautrat%20believed%20that%20she%20was%20witnessing%20a%20greenwashing%20operation%20of%20epic%20proportions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20some%20of%20United%20Oils'%20enablers%2C%20including%20Isaac%20Huam%C3%A1n%2C%20were%20sentenced%20to%20prison%20for%20obstruction%20of%20justice.%20But%20the%20plantations%20were%20receiving%20fresh%20investment%3B%20Amerra%20brought%20a%20crop%20consultant%20over%20from%20England%2C%20and%20the%20shareholders%20put%20their%20money%20into%20building%20a%20state-of-the-art%20mill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Spoor%20was%20hired%20in%202019%20after%20being%20recommended%20by%20an%20old%20friend%2C%20Joseph%20Massoud%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Anholt.%20Spoor%20said%20the%20overlap%20in%20employment%20in%20the%20company%20was%20not%20%26quot%3Bsurprising%20or%20suspicious%26quot%3B%20given%20how%20few%20qualified%20professionals%20are%20available%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20his%20first%20acts%20after%20taking%20the%20company's%20helm%20was%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20Melka.%20%26quot%3BI%20went%20to%20the%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20'I%20don't%20think%20we%20have%20a%20chance%20of%20success%20if%20he%20remains%20associated%20with%20the%20project%2C'%26quot%3B%20Spoor%20told%20me.%20The%20company%20bought%20out%20Melka's%20shares%20and%20ended%20his%20consulting%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20Spoor%20and%20the%20company's%20lawyers%20worked%20to%20get%20the%20%242.5%20million%20in%20fines%20the%20company%20owed%20to%20government%20agencies%20overturned.%20In%20order%20to%20get%20the%20land%20reclassified%20as%20farmland%2C%20they%20had%20to%20pay%20the%20state%20approximately%20%24450%2C000%20to%20cover%20harvest%20rights%20for%20the%20timber%20that%20Melka%20had%20chopped%20down.%20In%20any%20event%2C%20Spoor%20thought%20he%20was%20making%20progress%20toward%20resolving%20the%20outstanding%20claims%20against%20the%20company.%20Then%2C%20in%202022%2C%20Peru's%20comptroller%20general%20released%20three%20audits%2C%20concluding%20that%2C%20despite%20the%20agency%20reversals%20Spoor%20had%20orchestrated%2C%20Ocho%20Sur's%20plantations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gob.pe%2Finstitucion%2Fcontraloria%2Fnoticias%2F692213-autoridad-forestal-de-ucayali-autorizo-irregularmente-el-uso-de-11-mil-hectareas-a-empresa-privada%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20never%20be%20brought%20into%20compliance%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20exis