health%20post%2C%20and%20a%20better%20road.%20%26quot%3BThanks%20to%20%3Cem%3Ela%20empresa%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewe%20have%20a%20line%20of%20communication%20to%20the%20internet%2C%26quot%3B%20Barbar%C3%A1n%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20turn%2C%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya%20had%20signed%20a%20pact%20with%20Ocho%20Sur%20to%20preserve%20its%20newly%20acquired%20forests%20for%20the%20next%2025%20years.%20It%20was%20a%20critical%20final%20step%20for%20Ocho%20Sur%20in%20legalizing%20its%20plantations.%20Since%20Melka%20had%20failed%20to%20preserve%2030%25%20of%20the%20forest%20he'd%20purchased%2C%20as%20required%20under%20Peruvian%20law%2C%20Spoor%20needed%20to%20offset%20the%20deforestation%20by%20guaranteeing%20conservation%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Salda%C3%B1a%20jumped%20in%20to%20explain%20that%20the%20conflict%20with%20the%20company%20had%20been%20blown%20out%20of%20proportion%20by%20the%20media%2C%20a%20woman%20emerged%20from%20the%20house%20next%20door%20and%20interrupted%20our%20conversation.%20%26quot%3BSe%C3%B1or%2C%20Ulises%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhy%20do%20you%20deny%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20There%20was%20an%20awkward%20moment%20as%20Salda%C3%B1a%20calmly%20ignored%20her%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20community%20fully%20supported%20Ocho%20Sur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20later%20learned%20that%20the%20woman%20was%20the%20daughter-in-law%20of%20a%20woman%20named%20Luisa%20Mori%20Gonz%C3%A1lez%2C%20who%20heads%20an%20organization%20made%20up%20of%20the%20resistance%20%E2%80%94%20a%20group%20of%2010%20or%20so%20families%20who%20remained%20opposed%20to%20Ocho%20Sur%20and%20didn't%20share%20Barbar%C3%A1n's%20rosy%20assessment%20of%20the%20community's%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Luisa%20Mori%20Gonzales%20in%20her%20home%20with%20one%20of%20her%20children%20on%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762e3316c531c315b88e9c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELuisa%20Mori%20Gonz%C3%A1les%20at%20home%20in%20Santa%20Clara%20de%20Uchunya.%20She%20leads%20a%20group%20of%2010%20families%20who%20remain%20opposed%20to%20Ocho%20Sur.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20Mori%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20house%2C%20seated%20at%20a%20table%20near%20a%20wood%20fire%20stove%2C%20where%20a%20splayed%20possum%20was%20about%20to%20be%20cooked%20in%20a%20blackened%20pot.%20She%20expressed%20indignation%20about%20the%20pact%20the%20community%20had%20signed%20with%20the%20company%2C%20saying%20they%20were%20still%20a%20long%20way%20away%20from%20securing%20enough%20forest%20for%20their%20own%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20are%20we%20going%20to%20work%20during%20the%20next%2025%20years%3F%20Where%20are%20we%20going%20to%20hunt%20animals%20like%20this%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20gesturing%20to%20the%20stove.%20Though%20the%20agreement%20with%20Ocho%20Sur%20allowed%20hunting%20and%20gathering%20in%20the%20forest%2C%20she%20said%20too%20many%20natural%20resources%20had%20already%20been%20lost.%20It%20was%20no%20longer%20possible%2C%20she%20said%2C%20to%20find%20the%20apacharama%20tree%2C%20whose%20bark%20was%20traditionally%20burned%20to%20ash%20and%20used%20in%20pottery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20taking%20this%20position%20so%20as%20not%20to%20be%20tricked%20by%20the%20businessmen%2C%20the%20millionaire%20entities%20that%20are%20going%20to%20fool%20us%20with%201%20kilo%2C%202%20kilos%20of%20rice%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20At%20stake%2C%20she%20said%2C%20was%20the%20future%20of%20the%20community.%20%26quot%3BLife%20is%20not%20bought%20%E2%80%94%20life%20is%20borrowed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BJust%20as%20my%20ancestors%20left%20our%20territory%20for%20me%2C%20so%20I%20am%20going%20to%20leave%20it%20to%20my%20children%20and%20to%20my%20grandchildren.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20day%2C%20Spoor%20and%20I%20met%20for%20lunch%20at%20a%20cabana%20with%20a%20palm-thatch%20roof%20overlooking%20the%20dark%20waters%20of%20Tibecocha%20Lake.%20It's%20a%20lovely%20spot%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20property%20where%20Spoor%20has%20brought%20many%20of%20his%20influential%20guests.%20As%20the%20company%20chef%20prepared%20us%20a%20meal%20of%20risotto%20and%20breaded%20arapaima%2C%20an%20Amazonian%20fish%2C%20we%20leaned%20against%20the%20railing%2C%20gazed%20out%20at%20the%20forest%20on%20the%20opposite%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20me%20he%20was%20proud%20to%20have%20opened%20a%20new%20weigh%20station%20to%20purchase%20palm%20fruits%20from%20farms%20it%20has%20verified%20as%20deforestation-free.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20literally%20a%20cash%20register%20for%20farmers%2C%26quot%3B%20Spoor%20said.%20%26quot%3BFarmers%20who%20used%20to%20grow%20coca%20leaves%20are%20happy%20to%20switch%20to%20palm%20oil.%26quot%3B%20Peru's%20ministry%20of%20agriculture%20liked%20the%20idea%20enough%20to%20finance%20families%20seeking%20to%20grow%20oil%20palm%20for%20Ocho%20Sur%20and%20other%20local%20mills%20on%20previously%20degraded%20land.%20Diane%20Farrell%2C%20the%20US%20deputy%20undersecretary%20of%20international%20trade%2C%20even%20attended%20a%20launch%20event%20at%20Ocho%20Sur's%20nursery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Spoor%20and%20I%20talked%2C%20I%20noticed%20a%20fresh%20clearing%20in%20the%20lakeside%20forest%2C%20where%20rice%20shoots%20were%20sprouting%20from%20the%20soggy%20soil.%20It%20had%20been%20leveled%20just%20six%20months%20earlier%20by%20farmers%20from%20Esperanza%2C%20who%20had%20once%20sought%20to%20grow%20oil%20palm%20for%20Melka.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20devastating%20surprise%2C%26quot%3B%20Spoor%20said.%20He%20had%20been%20hoping%2C%20he%20said%2C%20to%20conserve%20that%20land%20to%20add%20to%20the%20company's%20offsets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Melka's%20arrival%20in%202010%2C%20the%20Ucayali%20region%20has%20experienced%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20deforestation%20in%20Peru.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20land-clearing%20on%20Tibecocha%20and%20Zanja%20Seca%2C%20one%20study%20documented%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0305750X18301207%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6%2C000%20acres%20of%20forest%3C%2Fa%3E%20destroyed%20from%202011%20to%202016%20by%20four%20communities%20that%20now%20grow%20oil%20palm%20on%20some%20of%20those%20lands%20for%20Ocho%20Sur.%20Coca%20farming%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20increased%20by%20a%20factor%20of%20five.%20Researchers%20who%20have%20evaluated%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20USAID%20and%20UN%20eradication%20programs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjied.lse.ac.uk%2Farticles%2F10.31389%2Fjied.92%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcluded%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20they%20had%20produced%20some%20benefits%2C%20they%20sometimes%20pushed%20%26quot%3Bmarginalized%20coca%20growers%20into%20more%20precarious%20positions%2C%20often%20leading%20them%20to%20replant%20coca%20in%20more%20distant%20forests.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20USAID%20told%20me%20that%20the%20agency%20now%20works%20to%20limit%20deforestation%20by%20helping%20small%20coffee%20and%20cacao%20growers%20increase%20production%20and%20that%20the%20US%20government%20%26quot%3Bwill%20continue%20to%20partner%20with%20and%20strengthen%20institutional%20capabilities%20of%20Peruvian%20agencies%20involved%20in%20counternarcotics%20efforts.%26quot%3B%20Candice%20Welsch%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20UN%20Office%20on%20Drugs%20and%20Crime%20in%20the%20Andean%20region%2C%20said%20the%20office's%20strategies%20had%20evolved%20in%20the%20decade%20since%20Hans-Jochen%20Wiese%20was%20leading%20alternative%20development.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20UN%20approved%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unodc.org%2Frddb%2Fdocument%2Fdrugs%2Fresolution%2F2022%2F65%2F65-1%2Fp2022_cnd_resolution_651ppromoting_alternative_development_as_a_development-oriented_drug_control_strategy_taking_into_account_measures_to_protect_the_environment.html%3Flng%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20prioritizing%20biodiversity%20protection%20in%20its%20development%20work.%20%26quot%3BWe%20never%20advocate%20for%20monocultures%2C%26quot%3B%20Welsch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20Spoor%20recently%20how%20Ocho%20Sur%20could%20ever%20escape%20the%20land-clearing%20its%20plantations%20were%20built%20upon%2C%20he%20challenged%20me%20to%20identify%20anyone%20in%20the%20region%20who%20was%20truly%20worse%20off%20because%20of%20it%20today.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20think%2010%20years%20from%20now%2C%2020%20years%20from%20now%2C%20people%20will%20say%20this%20is%20a%20tragedy%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20puzzled%20by%20this%20ideology%20that%20wants%20to%20keep%20people%20in%20poverty.%26quot%3B%20He%20told%20me%20he%20hoped%20my%20story%20would%20focus%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bparadox%20of%20human%20progress%26quot%3B%20and%20show%20how%20%26quot%3Beven%20amidst%20despair%2C%20seeds%20for%20a%20better%20future%20can%20take%20root.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20lighted%20palm%20tree%20at%20night%20in%20Shambo%20Porvenir%2C%20Peru.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6762e5785cddac6581d69aa5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20mature%20oil%20palm%20in%20Shambo%20Porvenir.%3Cp%3EFlorence%20Goupil%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Ocho%20Sur%2C%20achieving%20that%20dream%20has%20meant%20erasing%20history.%20The%20company%20has%20vigorously%20challenged%20its%20inclusion%20in%20Rod%C3%A1s'%20criminal%20case%20against%20Melka%2C%20filing%20a%20countersuit%20claiming%20that%20the%20prosecutor%20had%20overstepped%20his%20powers%20and%20engaged%20in%20%26quot%3Bideological%20persecution.%26quot%3B%20Rod%C3%A1s'%20office%20told%20me%20formal%20charges%20were%20imminent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20real%20battle%20over%20the%20company's%20future%20and%20the%20definition%20of%20deforestation%20has%20already%20shifted%20from%20the%20courts%20to%20the%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20Peruvian%20lawmakers%20granted%20amnesty%20to%20landowners%20who%2C%20like%20Melka%2C%20had%20cleared%20their%20land%20without%20first%20obtaining%20the%20change-of-use%20authorization.%20Supporters%20of%20the%20new%20law%20have%20said%20it%20will%20help%20formalize%20the%20farming%20sector%2C%20but%20the%20move%20has%20been%20challenged%20in%20court%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20could%20worsen%20conflicts%20between%20settlers%20and%20Indigenous%20communities.%20Fighting%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20amnesty%20is%20a%20familiar%20name%3A%20Washington%20Bol%C3%ADvar.%20He%20is%20represented%20in%20these%20efforts%20by%20the%20law%20firm%20Estudio%20Ghersi%2C%20which%20is%20also%20defending%20Ocho%20Sur%20in%20the%20criminal%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20obstacles%20to%20Ocho%20Sur%20coming%20into%20full%20compliance%20with%20Peruvian%20law%20is%20its%20lack%20of%20an%20approved%20environmental%20management%20plan%2C%20but%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fojo-publico.com%2Fambiente%2Fterritorio-amazonas%2Fempresas-sin-permiso-ambiental-podran-acogerse-nuevo-reglamento%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%20regulation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20enacted%20in%20June%2C%20gave%20companies%20across%20the%20Peruvian%20Amazon%20a%20chance%20to%20retroactively%20obtain%20the%20needed%20approvals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20after%20my%20visit%2C%20the%20Amazon%20was%20engulfed%20by%20record%20wildfires%20that%20incinerated%20over%20a%20hundred%20million%20acres%20of%20rainforest.%20The%20forests%20of%20Ucayali%20were%20among%20those%20going%20up%20in%20flames.%20In%20a%20climate%20of%20impunity%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.