port%20her%20parents.%20After%20working%20in%20several%20hospitals%2C%20she%20eventually%20opened%20her%20own%20clinic.%20She%20came%20in%20contact%20with%20Talal%20Abdo%20Mahdi%20in%202014%20to%20open%20her%20own%20establishment%2C%20as%20local%20law%20mandates%20partnering%20with%20a%20local%20to%20start%20a%20business%20in%20Yemen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20troubles%20arose%20between%20the%20duo%2C%20Nimisha%20filed%20a%20police%20complaint%20against%20Mahdi%20due%20to%20which%20he%20was%20arrested%20in%202016.%20But%20after%20his%20release%2C%20he%20continued%20threatening%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20a%20dispute%20arose%20between%20her%20and%20her%20Yemeni%20business%20partner%20Mahdi%2C%20after%20she%20opposed%20his%20alleged%20attempts%20to%20misappropriate%20funds.%20Nimisha's%20family%20claimed%20that%20she%20allegedly%20injected%20Mahdi%20with%20sedatives%20to%20retrieve%20her%20confiscated%20passport.%20However%2C%20an%20overdose%20led%20to%20his%20death.%20She%20was%20arrested%20while%20attempting%20to%20flee%20the%20country%20and%20was%20convicted%20of%20murder%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20a%20trial%20court%20in%20Sanaa%20sentenced%20her%20to%20death%2C%20and%20Yemen's%20Supreme%20Judicial%20Council%20upheld%20the%20verdict%20in%20November%202023%2C%20though%20it%20left%20open%20the%20option%20of%20blood%20money%2C%20which%20is%20the%20compensation%20to%20be%20decided%20by%20the%20victim's%20family.%20They%20approached%20the%20Yemini%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20trial%20court's%20order%2C%20but%20their%20appeal%20was%20rejected%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Was%20Nimisha%20Sentenced%20To%20Death%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYemeni%20law%20imposes%20a%20death%20penalty%20for%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20offenses%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bviolating%20the%20independence%2C%20unity%20or%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20the%20Republic%2C%26quot%3B%20undertaking%20%26quot%3Ban%20act%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20weakening%20the%20armed%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20murder%2C%20drug%20trafficking%2C%20adultery%2C%20consensual%20same-sex%20sexual%20activity%20between%20adults%2C%20turning%20back%20from%20or%20denouncing%20Islam%2C%20and%20facilitating%20prostitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Followed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENimisha's%20mother%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20house%20help%20for%20a%20family%20in%20Kochi%2C%20has%20sold%20her%20property%20to%20fight%20the%20case%2C%20said%20lawyer%20Subhash%20Chandran%2C%20who%20is%20part%20of%20the%20forum%20comprising%20politicians%2C%20businessmen%2C%20activists%2C%20and%20expatriates%20seeking%20justice%20for%20Nimisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20relentless%20efforts%20to%20secure%20a%20waiver%20of%20Nimisha's%20death%20penalty%2C%20her%20mother%20Prema%20Kumari%20travelled%20to%20Yemen's%20capital%20Sanaa%20earlier%20this%20year%20to%20negotiate%20the%20payment%20of%20diya%20(blood%20money)%20to%20the%20victim's%20family%20with%20the%20assistance%20of%20the%20Save%20Nimisha%20Priya%20International%20Action%20Council%2C%20an%20organisation%20of%20NRI%20social%20workers%20based%20in%20Yemen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalks%20to%20negotiate%20the%20blood%20money%20with%20the%20victim's%20family%20had%20come%20to%20an%20abrupt%20halt%20in%20September%20after%20Abdullah%20Ameer%2C%20the%20lawyer%20appointed%20by%20the%20Indian%20Embassy%2C%20demanded%20a%20pre-negotiation%20fee%20of%20%2420%2C000%20(approximately%20Rs%2016.6%20lakh)%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20Manorama%20online.%20MEA%20has%20already%20provided%20%2419%2C871%20to%20Ameer%20in%20July%2C%20but%20he%20insisted%20on%20a%20total%20fee%20of%20%2440%2C000%2C%20payable%20in%20two%20instalments%20before%20he%20would%20resume%20talks.%20The%20Save%20Nimisha%20Priya%20International%20Action%20Council%20succeeded%20in%20raising%20the%20first%20instalment%20of%20Ameer's%20fee%20through%20crowdfunding.%20However%2C%20later%20they%20reportedly%20faced%20challenges%20in%20ensuring%20transparency%20to%20donors%20about%20how%20the%20funds%20were%20being%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735626780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F2pkplgcg_nimisha-priya_625x300_31_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-why-yemen-has-sanctioned-indian-nurses-death-sentence-7368341%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nimisha%20Priya%2C%20a%20nurse%20from%20Kollengode%20in%20Kerala's%20Palakkad%20district%2C%20had%20allegedly%20injected%20her%20business%20partner%20with%20sedatives%20to%20retrieve%20her%20confiscated%20passport%2C%20which%20led%20to%20his%20death.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-why-yemen-has-sanctioned-indian-nurses-death-sentence-7368341%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HBO%20and%20Cablevision%20founder%20Charles%20Dolan%20passes%20away%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735626719000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116820612%2Cimgsize-15082.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Fhbo-and-cablevision-founder-charles-dolan-passes-away-at-98%2Farticleshow%2F116820642.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F116820642.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ECharles%20Dolan%2C%20the%20visionary%20behind%20HBO%20and%20Cablevision%2C%20passed%20away%20at%2098.%20His%20significant%20contributions%20to%20the%20entertainment%20industry%20include%20founding%20HBO%20in%201972%2C%20Cablevision%20in%201973%2C%20and%20the%20American%20Movie%20Classics%20in%201984.%20Dolan%20is%20survived%20by%20six%20children%2C%2019%20grandchildren%2C%20and%20five%20great-grandchi